1
00:00:10,248 --> 00:00:14,905
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:54,466 --> 00:00:58,514
[BOOTS MARCHING]

3
00:01:02,996 --> 00:01:05,738
[BOMB WHISTLING, EXPLODING]

4
00:01:22,581 --> 00:01:25,062
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

5
00:01:59,401 --> 00:02:01,881
[SEAGULLS SQUAWKING]

6
00:02:02,186 --> 00:02:05,668
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

7
00:02:14,981 --> 00:02:16,548
Right there.

8
00:02:23,381 --> 00:02:24,774
[DOOR HANDLE RATTLES]

9
00:02:29,605 --> 00:02:32,608
[BUZZER BLARES]

10
00:02:34,827 --> 00:02:36,351
[DOOR HANDLE RATTLES]

11
00:02:39,005 --> 00:02:41,356
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

12
00:02:42,008 --> 00:02:43,053
[DOOR OPENING]

13
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:45,882
[PASSERBY GRUNTS SOFTLY]

14
00:02:56,936 --> 00:02:58,024
[SIGHS]

15
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,121
[BRIEFCASE SETTING DOWN]

16
00:03:19,437 --> 00:03:20,830
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

17
00:03:25,008 --> 00:03:26,662
[CONTINUES KNOCKING ON DOOR]

18
00:03:30,883 --> 00:03:32,581
MICHAEL: Mr. Bau, is that you?

19
00:03:32,755 --> 00:03:34,887
I'm not here. Go away!

20
00:03:35,105 --> 00:03:36,976
MICHAEL: Please,
I... I must speak with you.

21
00:03:37,063 --> 00:03:40,066
Uh, my name
is Michael Wancowski.

22
00:03:42,982 --> 00:03:45,333
I'm the attorney representing
the Plaszow prisoners.

23
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:46,725
JOSEPH: What's it this time?

24
00:03:46,812 --> 00:03:48,988
Are you going to sue
for an apology

25
00:03:49,075 --> 00:03:50,294
from the Nazi Party?

26
00:03:50,555 --> 00:03:54,211
Or maybe for back wages for time
spent working in camps?

27
00:03:54,429 --> 00:03:57,170
No, I'm suing for justice.

28
00:03:58,694 --> 00:04:00,652
A trial has been scheduled
against Franz Gruen.

29
00:04:00,913 --> 00:04:05,744
And we want,
we need, you to testify.

30
00:04:06,179 --> 00:04:08,356
This man
has been acquitted twice,

31
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:10,445
and he will always be acquitted.

32
00:04:10,532 --> 00:04:12,795
There is no proof
of the charges against him.

33
00:04:12,882 --> 00:04:15,363
And it doesn't matter if one
or a thousand of his victims

34
00:04:15,450 --> 00:04:18,017
comes forward, all he has to do
is smile and say,

35
00:04:18,148 --> 00:04:20,846
"Oh, it must have been
somebody else. It wasn't me."

36
00:04:20,933 --> 00:04:23,284
"It was that other
mass-murdering Nazi."

37
00:04:23,545 --> 00:04:24,937
And he's free.

38
00:04:25,024 --> 00:04:26,678
I promise you,
this time will be different.

39
00:04:28,593 --> 00:04:30,073
How can you promise me that?

40
00:04:32,902 --> 00:04:34,425
You don't know who I am?

41
00:04:34,512 --> 00:04:37,515
Of course I know who you are,
another attorney,

42
00:04:37,733 --> 00:04:39,996
who likes to milk his clients
for all they're worth.

43
00:04:40,083 --> 00:04:42,390
And at the end of a case,
nobody wins but you.

44
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,130
So, good day!

45
00:04:44,305 --> 00:04:46,568
MICHAEL: Okay, but Mr. Bau,
Mr. Bau, please.

46
00:04:49,179 --> 00:04:50,485
This is our chance.

47
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:55,185
Okay, here is how this will go.

48
00:04:57,143 --> 00:04:59,755
When I say "stop," you stop.

49
00:05:00,843 --> 00:05:03,062
And when I say "go," you go.

50
00:05:04,673 --> 00:05:05,630
You have my word.

51
00:05:05,761 --> 00:05:06,979
JOSEPH: Now go.

52
00:05:09,068 --> 00:05:10,635
MICHAEL:
Fear never stopped you before.

53
00:05:22,168 --> 00:05:23,692
[SIGHS, SNIFFS]

54
00:05:25,215 --> 00:05:26,259
[SMACKS LIPS]

55
00:05:27,957 --> 00:05:29,524
Would you like some tea?

56
00:05:29,915 --> 00:05:30,916
MICHAEL: Please.

57
00:05:31,047 --> 00:05:33,049
[WATER RUNNING]
[WATER POURING]

58
00:05:33,223 --> 00:05:37,009
JOSEPH: Would you mind, um,
turning off the faucet for me?

59
00:05:37,314 --> 00:05:38,315
Sure.

60
00:05:41,013 --> 00:05:42,319
Ah. [CHUCKLES]

61
00:05:47,716 --> 00:05:52,547
I've heard it said that art
is a reflection of the soul.

62
00:05:52,938 --> 00:05:54,026
Ah.

63
00:05:54,549 --> 00:05:56,986
Art critic and an attorney?

64
00:05:58,161 --> 00:05:59,554
Now, I'm really thrilled.

65
00:06:03,427 --> 00:06:04,515
Is this, um...

66
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:05,908
JOSEPH: Um.

67
00:06:06,474 --> 00:06:09,302
Did you come here to stare
at my walls or to talk to me?

68
00:06:10,042 --> 00:06:13,829
[EXHALES, CHUCKLES]
Yes. Well, uh...

69
00:06:15,439 --> 00:06:17,310
Do you mind if I record you?

70
00:06:18,050 --> 00:06:21,271
Have at it. [GROANS]

71
00:06:28,147 --> 00:06:31,716
This will take the place of me
having to appear in Vienna, huh?

72
00:06:32,325 --> 00:06:35,285
Well, having you in person
would be much more convincing.

73
00:06:41,204 --> 00:06:43,989
This is testimony
of Mr. Joseph Bau.

74
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:49,865
The State versus former SS Guard
Franz Gruen, October 1971.

75
00:06:52,171 --> 00:06:55,218
Now... Is that all right?

76
00:06:55,305 --> 00:06:57,438
Yes, very creative.
MICHAEL: Thank you.

77
00:06:59,396 --> 00:07:03,008
So, uh, your first encounter
with SS Guard Franz Gruen

78
00:07:03,095 --> 00:07:06,272
was in the Plaszow Camp.
So tell me....

79
00:07:06,359 --> 00:07:09,362
No. It was in my later days
at the ghetto,

80
00:07:10,581 --> 00:07:13,976
uh, when he was just a soldier
in the Nazi army.

81
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:18,763
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

82
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:31,950
[SEAGULLS SQUAWKING]

83
00:07:38,043 --> 00:07:39,523
WOMAN: [IN POLISH]
They're coming! Quickly!

84
00:07:39,610 --> 00:07:41,438
The trucks are coming!
[VEHICLES APPROACHING]

85
00:07:41,699 --> 00:07:44,789
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

86
00:07:47,226 --> 00:07:50,969
[WOMAN SCREAMS]
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

87
00:07:51,274 --> 00:07:53,711
[IN GERMAN]
Leave your stuff. Move it!

88
00:07:53,929 --> 00:07:55,974
[SOLDIERS SPEAKING GERMAN]

89
00:07:59,935 --> 00:08:04,635
[SOLDIERS SPEAKING GERMAN]

90
00:08:05,201 --> 00:08:08,160
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR]

91
00:08:08,465 --> 00:08:10,902
[ENGINE REVVING]

92
00:08:27,005 --> 00:08:29,312
[BELL TOLLING]

93
00:08:32,097 --> 00:08:35,100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

94
00:08:38,495 --> 00:08:40,018
[CAR HONKING]

95
00:08:45,763 --> 00:08:48,157
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

96
00:08:48,897 --> 00:08:51,203
[SOLDIER SPEAKING GERMAN]
[BABY CRYING]

97
00:08:57,470 --> 00:08:58,559
[BRAKES SCREECHING]

98
00:09:13,399 --> 00:09:18,317
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

99
00:09:19,797 --> 00:09:21,756
Your papers. Next!

100
00:09:22,017 --> 00:09:23,584
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

101
00:09:26,717 --> 00:09:28,110
Hat off.

102
00:09:30,112 --> 00:09:32,810
[SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

103
00:09:38,903 --> 00:09:40,513
[IN ENGLISH] Oh. I'm sorry, sir.

104
00:09:40,949 --> 00:09:44,082
[IN GERMAN] Sorry?
You Jewish pig! How dare you?

105
00:09:45,257 --> 00:09:46,389
Show me your I.D. card.

106
00:09:46,781 --> 00:09:50,132
[IN ENGLISH] Uh, I'm sorry, sir,
I do not speak German, um...

107
00:09:50,915 --> 00:09:53,309
I'm on my way
to the administration offices.

108
00:09:53,570 --> 00:09:54,832
Get to your feet!
[FINGERS SNAPPING]

109
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:56,399
JOSEPH: I'm on my way--
Show me your
Kennkarte.

110
00:09:56,660 --> 00:10:00,403
Uh, perhaps you could take it up
with your, um, Untersturmführer?

111
00:10:01,186 --> 00:10:02,361
I can what?

112
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:04,886
You can kiss my ass,
you piece of shit!

113
00:10:04,973 --> 00:10:06,627
[GUNFIRE]
As you like. [KISSES]

114
00:10:07,453 --> 00:10:08,803
Mm. [SMACKS LIPS]

115
00:10:10,935 --> 00:10:11,936
You didn't.

116
00:10:12,197 --> 00:10:14,199
Is this my deposition or yours?

117
00:10:14,722 --> 00:10:17,376
Yours.
I kissed him, on the cheek.

118
00:10:17,463 --> 00:10:19,596
MICHAEL: Uh-huh.
And ran.

119
00:10:20,031 --> 00:10:21,816
[SOLDIERS LAUGH]

120
00:10:22,686 --> 00:10:23,992
[BYSTANDERS SCREAM]

121
00:10:27,212 --> 00:10:29,171
JOSEPH: Whoa. Sorry, so sorry.
[EXCLAIMS]

122
00:10:32,304 --> 00:10:34,132
Your hat![GRUNTS]

123
00:10:35,481 --> 00:10:36,526
[SIGHS]

124
00:10:37,266 --> 00:10:38,484
[IN HEBREW] Crazy.

125
00:10:38,659 --> 00:10:41,226
[PANTS]

126
00:10:43,011 --> 00:10:44,447
NATHANIEL: Joseph...
[GRUNTS]

127
00:10:46,362 --> 00:10:48,190
[IN ENGLISH] Nathaniel,
they stopped me.

128
00:10:48,277 --> 00:10:50,192
[PANTS]
I thought I was a dead man.

129
00:10:50,279 --> 00:10:52,673
You look alive to me, my friend.
Do you have the IDs?

130
00:10:54,892 --> 00:10:58,200
[PANTS, CHUCKLES]

131
00:10:58,722 --> 00:11:00,637
Well done.
Excellent work, thank you.

132
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:02,552
No, no, no, no, no.

133
00:11:02,726 --> 00:11:05,250
Thank you.
For letting me do this.

134
00:11:05,773 --> 00:11:08,950
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:11:25,401 --> 00:11:27,011
It's healing nicely.

136
00:11:27,098 --> 00:11:29,797
My dear,
why do your waste your time

137
00:11:29,884 --> 00:11:31,929
on someone like me?

138
00:11:32,669 --> 00:11:34,497
If a gentleman
is attractive enough,

139
00:11:34,584 --> 00:11:38,109
it is never a waste
of a lady's time. [CHUCKLES]

140
00:11:39,023 --> 00:11:40,895
Now, you stay off that foot.

141
00:11:41,025 --> 00:11:43,114
Yeah.
And away from trouble.

142
00:11:43,811 --> 00:11:46,639
You keep that hat.
Looks gorgeous on you.

143
00:11:48,076 --> 00:11:49,077
[SIGHS]

144
00:11:53,211 --> 00:11:55,953
[BABY CRYING]
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

145
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,346
BYSTANDER: Shalom, Joseph.

146
00:12:06,485 --> 00:12:09,358
[CHANTING IN HEBREW]

147
00:12:21,718 --> 00:12:23,241
[IN ENGLISH] Hey, hey. Hey!

148
00:12:26,418 --> 00:12:27,506
Mama.

149
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:30,553
Shabbat Shalom, Joseph.

150
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:31,815
ABRAHAM: You're late.

151
00:12:32,555 --> 00:12:34,775
You aren't still forging IDs,
are you?

152
00:12:34,905 --> 00:12:36,602
Joseph, I've told you--
CYLA: Hey.

153
00:12:36,907 --> 00:12:40,128
What kind of Shabbat blessing
is that, Abraham?

154
00:12:40,519 --> 00:12:42,565
No, Papa. Just maps.

155
00:12:43,218 --> 00:12:45,394
You can't get into trouble
for that. Not yet.

156
00:12:45,524 --> 00:12:47,613
Anything you do
for the Resistance

157
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:49,050
can get you in trouble.

158
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:53,794
Already, half the ghetto
has been deported to work camps.

159
00:12:54,055 --> 00:12:56,013
Stop being such a coward,
Abraham.

160
00:12:56,144 --> 00:12:58,973
Anything this boy can do
to help our people fight back,

161
00:12:59,060 --> 00:13:00,061
you should be proud of him.

162
00:13:00,148 --> 00:13:01,758
This is a family matter.

163
00:13:01,932 --> 00:13:04,326
We may be forced to live
in this small room together,

164
00:13:04,456 --> 00:13:06,023
but you are not family.

165
00:13:06,676 --> 00:13:08,199
You think you are a hero.

166
00:13:08,373 --> 00:13:11,681
As if you should be complemented
for being courageous.

167
00:13:11,768 --> 00:13:14,684
But actually, all you are doing
is risking your life,

168
00:13:14,771 --> 00:13:16,512
and the lives of your family.

169
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:19,645
I'm just trying
to give people hope.

170
00:13:19,776 --> 00:13:21,778
Exactly how will you do that?

171
00:13:21,865 --> 00:13:23,606
By reminding people that
there are some things

172
00:13:23,736 --> 00:13:25,216
that they can't take from us.

173
00:13:25,477 --> 00:13:29,220
Laughter, joy, our spirits.

174
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:33,311
And we are not helpless.
These are just men with guns.

175
00:13:33,442 --> 00:13:34,573
Just?

176
00:13:34,965 --> 00:13:38,882
Stop persecuting him, Abraham.
We have Nazis for that.

177
00:13:39,361 --> 00:13:40,405
[EXHALES]

178
00:13:40,841 --> 00:13:43,060
Forgive me for thinking
it's important we keep believing

179
00:13:43,147 --> 00:13:44,757
there's more beyond all this.

180
00:13:44,888 --> 00:13:45,889
[CYLA CHUCKLES]

181
00:13:45,976 --> 00:13:49,414
You have any new movies
to show us?

182
00:13:51,590 --> 00:13:54,028
[BOTH GIGGLE]

183
00:13:54,332 --> 00:13:57,248
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:14:11,219 --> 00:14:13,003
ABRAHAM: No!
[BOTH LAUGH]

185
00:14:13,090 --> 00:14:14,091
Burn it!

186
00:14:14,613 --> 00:14:17,965
These drawings will be
a death sentence for us all!

187
00:14:20,402 --> 00:14:22,056
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

188
00:14:23,796 --> 00:14:25,886
Your fear
is their greatest weapon.

189
00:14:26,277 --> 00:14:28,801
It's the first weapon
that we need to take from them.

190
00:14:30,629 --> 00:14:33,632
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

191
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:39,900
[DOOR OPENING]

192
00:14:42,859 --> 00:14:46,123
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

193
00:14:49,518 --> 00:14:52,303
I just want you to know,
I'm very proud of you.

194
00:14:53,130 --> 00:14:55,916
I don't think anyone,
even your father,

195
00:14:56,090 --> 00:14:59,136
could damage your optimism.
Thankfully.

196
00:14:59,789 --> 00:15:02,923
Because hope is in high demand
these days. Hmm?

197
00:15:03,793 --> 00:15:04,794
[KISSES]

198
00:15:12,628 --> 00:15:13,629
[DOOR CLOSING]

199
00:15:13,759 --> 00:15:16,588
[SNORING]

200
00:15:19,852 --> 00:15:21,637
[MUSIC FADES]

201
00:15:22,507 --> 00:15:25,597
[ENGINES RUMBLING]

202
00:15:25,815 --> 00:15:28,035
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:15:28,165 --> 00:15:29,688
Wake up! Trucks are coming!

204
00:15:29,775 --> 00:15:32,561
Trucks are coming, wake up.
Hurry! Hey!

205
00:15:32,648 --> 00:15:36,695
[ALL CLAMORING]

206
00:15:36,782 --> 00:15:39,089
And what, we should outrun them?

207
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:44,616
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

208
00:15:45,530 --> 00:15:46,967
[AUTOMATIC GUNFIRE]

209
00:15:47,532 --> 00:15:49,970
[RESIDENTS SCREAMING]

210
00:15:50,057 --> 00:15:51,841
[IN ENGLISH]
Joseph, do what they say.

211
00:15:51,972 --> 00:15:54,452
Do not give them
a reason to harm us.

212
00:15:55,845 --> 00:15:57,325
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

213
00:15:57,412 --> 00:15:59,109
Move it or you will be shot!

214
00:15:59,631 --> 00:16:02,895
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR]

215
00:16:06,421 --> 00:16:08,510
[GUNFIRE CONTINUES]
[RESIDENTS SCREAMING]

216
00:16:10,338 --> 00:16:12,035
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

217
00:16:14,472 --> 00:16:16,083
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

218
00:16:17,693 --> 00:16:19,173
Hey.
[SOLDIER GRUNTS]

219
00:16:19,521 --> 00:16:21,653
[BELL TOLLING]

220
00:16:24,308 --> 00:16:29,444
[OFFICER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

221
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:32,621
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:16:38,061 --> 00:16:40,063
[PRISONERS GRUNTING]

223
00:16:44,546 --> 00:16:48,463
[REBECCA GRUNTING, PANTING]

224
00:16:52,858 --> 00:16:53,772
[GRUNTS]

225
00:16:56,819 --> 00:16:59,126
[GRUNTS, PANTS]

226
00:17:05,915 --> 00:17:07,264
[GRUNTS]

227
00:17:09,788 --> 00:17:11,660
ALEKSY: [IN ENGLISH]
You pick up the smaller one.

228
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:13,053
I'll pick up the larger.

229
00:17:16,143 --> 00:17:18,232
[GRUNTS]

230
00:17:26,718 --> 00:17:28,938
ANIA: This is all the bread
I can get today.

231
00:17:30,853 --> 00:17:32,072
Ania, stop.

232
00:17:33,073 --> 00:17:34,161
Everyone is starving.

233
00:17:35,118 --> 00:17:37,599
But, we are all we have left.

234
00:17:37,816 --> 00:17:39,253
I have to do what I can.

235
00:17:39,905 --> 00:17:42,734
Mama would have done the same.
You know that, little brother.

236
00:17:45,781 --> 00:17:48,044
Thank you. What's your name?

237
00:17:48,436 --> 00:17:51,091
My name is Aleksy. And you are?

238
00:17:51,613 --> 00:17:52,657
Joseph.

239
00:17:53,223 --> 00:17:55,399
How did you land
in this lap of misery?

240
00:17:55,486 --> 00:17:58,272
Forgive the obvious,
but you don't exactly blend in.

241
00:17:59,447 --> 00:18:01,449
My father was the wrong color.

242
00:18:01,927 --> 00:18:03,842
Well, how dare he?

243
00:18:06,497 --> 00:18:07,542
[CHUCKLES]

244
00:18:11,894 --> 00:18:16,203
[SOBS INTENSELY]

245
00:18:17,204 --> 00:18:19,336
She's my mom! [SOBS]

246
00:18:19,554 --> 00:18:22,122
[CONTINUES SOBBING]

247
00:18:24,472 --> 00:18:26,213
And what do we have here?

248
00:18:26,517 --> 00:18:28,693
He says it's his mother's grave.

249
00:18:28,867 --> 00:18:31,957
[PRISONER SOBS]
Hmm. Sad.

250
00:18:34,046 --> 00:18:35,309
[GUNSHOT]

251
00:18:35,613 --> 00:18:36,962
[HORSE NEIGHS]

252
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:40,923
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:18:43,795 --> 00:18:46,363
[IN GERMAN]
You two. Take him to the pit.

254
00:18:46,798 --> 00:18:48,278
Back to work!

255
00:18:53,762 --> 00:18:57,069
[IN ENGLISH]
Prisoner number 69084!

256
00:18:58,854 --> 00:19:00,682
You are wanted
by the Kommandant.

257
00:19:01,552 --> 00:19:03,511
Follow me
to the administration office.

258
00:19:20,397 --> 00:19:21,485
That way.

259
00:19:31,669 --> 00:19:32,670
Name?

260
00:19:32,844 --> 00:19:34,455
Uh. Joseph Bau.

261
00:19:38,850 --> 00:19:40,635
Glad to make your acquaintance.

262
00:19:40,765 --> 00:19:42,463
[GUNSHOT]
[HEAVY THUD]

263
00:19:43,638 --> 00:19:45,466
[IN HEBREW]
Blessed is the judge of truth.

264
00:19:46,206 --> 00:19:48,556
GOETH: [IN ENGLISH]
Mietek, get in here! Schnell!

265
00:19:55,215 --> 00:19:56,390
Best to keep your eyes down.

266
00:19:56,825 --> 00:19:58,870
He doesn't usually kill twice
in the same hour.

267
00:20:02,352 --> 00:20:05,094
[CLOCK TICKING]

268
00:20:07,792 --> 00:20:09,098
I can't believe it.

269
00:20:10,404 --> 00:20:11,535
Such a tragedy.

270
00:20:13,363 --> 00:20:14,625
The carpet is ruined.

271
00:20:14,930 --> 00:20:16,236
[CIGARETTE CRACKLING]

272
00:20:17,411 --> 00:20:18,412
Why are you here?

273
00:20:18,977 --> 00:20:20,805
Your new mapmaker, Kommandant.

274
00:20:20,979 --> 00:20:23,547
Hmm. Is that what you are?

275
00:20:24,853 --> 00:20:26,028
JOSEPH: Well, uh...

276
00:20:26,376 --> 00:20:27,464
I have a degree

277
00:20:27,551 --> 00:20:29,945
from the Academy
of Fine Arts in Krakow, uh,

278
00:20:30,337 --> 00:20:32,252
I'm skilled in cartography,

279
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:34,863
Gothic lettering, drafting--
Hmm.

280
00:20:36,343 --> 00:20:37,866
Gothic lettering?

281
00:20:38,736 --> 00:20:40,390
JOSEPH: Yes, gothic lettering.

282
00:20:41,304 --> 00:20:42,653
That was actually my specialty.

283
00:20:44,438 --> 00:20:45,482
Then you could be of service.

284
00:20:46,657 --> 00:20:48,790
How fortunate. [CHUCKLES]
For you.

285
00:20:50,182 --> 00:20:52,141
Mietek, get me a new carpet.

286
00:20:52,663 --> 00:20:55,057
And a manicurist that knows
how to cut some damn cuticles.

287
00:20:55,144 --> 00:20:56,754
Yes, sir.

288
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,584
[GUNSHOT AND SHOUTING
IN DISTANCE]

289
00:21:00,671 --> 00:21:02,107
[DOOR CLOSING]
MIETEK: Are you all right?

290
00:21:03,674 --> 00:21:04,893
How do you do this?

291
00:21:05,589 --> 00:21:08,679
I try to focus on each moment
as if it's my last.

292
00:21:09,724 --> 00:21:11,334
How does that help you?

293
00:21:12,030 --> 00:21:13,205
[GUNSHOT IN DISTANCE]

294
00:21:19,299 --> 00:21:21,213
[GASPS] Oh!

295
00:21:21,344 --> 00:21:22,954
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

296
00:21:23,041 --> 00:21:24,173
[JOSEPH EXHALES]

297
00:21:25,130 --> 00:21:27,524
You really pull some strings.

298
00:21:27,611 --> 00:21:29,700
I wanted to make sure
you had all you needed,

299
00:21:29,787 --> 00:21:31,223
to keep you alive.

300
00:21:31,311 --> 00:21:34,705
Time to put your special
ID forgery talents to good use.

301
00:21:34,836 --> 00:21:38,230
We have an office
where you can work your magic.

302
00:21:43,061 --> 00:21:45,107
Wow. These are brand new.

303
00:21:45,194 --> 00:21:47,152
MIETEK: They are. The best.

304
00:21:51,156 --> 00:21:52,854
[EXCLAIMS]
[MIETEK CHUCKLES]

305
00:21:55,335 --> 00:21:57,380
Nathaniel!
[NATHANIEL CHUCKLES]

306
00:21:58,555 --> 00:22:00,644
This is my brother,
Itzhak Stern.

307
00:22:01,079 --> 00:22:02,994
I told him of your involvement
in the Resistance.

308
00:22:03,081 --> 00:22:04,082
He wanted to meet you.

309
00:22:04,387 --> 00:22:05,823
He's Oskar Schindler's
accountant.

310
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:07,172
Privilege to meet you.

311
00:22:07,259 --> 00:22:09,044
Who is Oskar Schindler?

312
00:22:09,131 --> 00:22:10,872
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

313
00:22:16,181 --> 00:22:17,661
[IN ENGLISH]
I'll let you two talk.

314
00:22:18,009 --> 00:22:19,489
Need to get back to my work

315
00:22:19,576 --> 00:22:20,925
before the guards
come looking for me.

316
00:22:25,190 --> 00:22:26,670
Mind if I join you?

317
00:22:26,801 --> 00:22:28,280
Well I certainly hope
this office meets

318
00:22:28,368 --> 00:22:29,804
my extravagant standards.

319
00:22:29,891 --> 00:22:33,373
I can only do slave labor
for psychopathic monsters

320
00:22:33,503 --> 00:22:35,940
in, uh, a place
of absolute luxury.

321
00:22:36,027 --> 00:22:37,507
[MIETEK CHUCKLES]

322
00:22:37,594 --> 00:22:40,554
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

323
00:22:47,430 --> 00:22:48,562
[JOSEPH WHISTLES]

324
00:22:48,736 --> 00:22:49,824
Whoa.

325
00:22:50,128 --> 00:22:51,260
Ah, I already see

326
00:22:51,347 --> 00:22:52,827
that I'm going
to have complaints.

327
00:22:53,175 --> 00:22:54,742
I mean, where's my girl?

328
00:22:54,829 --> 00:22:57,092
No fan? No grapes?

329
00:22:57,745 --> 00:22:58,963
I don't know.

330
00:22:59,529 --> 00:23:02,402
Yeah, I may just have to
take it up with the little guy

331
00:23:02,532 --> 00:23:04,273
with the funny moustache

332
00:23:04,404 --> 00:23:06,928
and the tiniest pee-pee
in the known universe.

333
00:23:07,058 --> 00:23:08,799
Yeah, yeah, he holds the record.

334
00:23:12,977 --> 00:23:14,414
If we do our work,

335
00:23:14,718 --> 00:23:16,285
maybe we can survive
this madness

336
00:23:16,372 --> 00:23:17,286
and tell our story.

337
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,507
And the world needs to know.

338
00:23:25,729 --> 00:23:28,863
[JOSEPH INHALES DEEPLY,
EXHALES HEAVILY]

339
00:23:33,258 --> 00:23:36,610
Is it possible
to change my seat?

340
00:23:37,959 --> 00:23:40,265
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

341
00:23:46,228 --> 00:23:48,360
[IN HEBREW]
Blessed is the judge of truth.

342
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:55,150
[BELL TOLLING]

343
00:23:57,108 --> 00:24:00,242
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

344
00:24:07,945 --> 00:24:09,469
JOSEPH: [IN ENGLISH]
Look what I got here.

345
00:24:13,647 --> 00:24:16,040
I made that for the Kommandant.

346
00:24:16,258 --> 00:24:19,087
I show it to him before he goes
to bed every night.

347
00:24:19,174 --> 00:24:20,262
[ALEKSY CHUCKLING]

348
00:24:21,611 --> 00:24:24,005
JOSEPH: He likes that
and a glass of warm milk.

349
00:24:24,266 --> 00:24:26,311
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

350
00:24:26,398 --> 00:24:28,139
Better make a copy
for the Fuhrer,

351
00:24:28,488 --> 00:24:29,967
or he too will be jealous.

352
00:24:30,141 --> 00:24:31,229
JOSEPH: He may be.

353
00:24:31,447 --> 00:24:36,800
[GROUP CHUCKLES]

354
00:24:37,105 --> 00:24:38,410
All right, all right,
give it to me

355
00:24:38,498 --> 00:24:41,631
before you get us all killed.
And the Kommandant,

356
00:24:41,936 --> 00:24:45,766
sometimes he can't go to sleep
at night. So, I help him.

357
00:24:46,506 --> 00:24:50,553
If he's not listening to me
or disobeying, I have no choice.

358
00:24:51,032 --> 00:24:53,425
I bend him over his office desk

359
00:24:53,513 --> 00:24:55,819
and I give him
a nice, good spanking.

360
00:24:55,906 --> 00:24:57,168
[ALL LAUGHING]

361
00:24:57,255 --> 00:24:58,866
And then boom, lights out.

362
00:25:01,346 --> 00:25:04,001
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]
[TRUCK ENGINE STARTING]

363
00:25:09,529 --> 00:25:11,748
And we are where?
We are here, sir.

364
00:25:11,922 --> 00:25:13,620
[DOG WHIMPERS]

365
00:25:14,316 --> 00:25:17,362
But in a certain sense,
where are any of us, really?

366
00:25:18,233 --> 00:25:19,364
Nietzsche.

367
00:25:20,540 --> 00:25:21,541
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

368
00:25:21,715 --> 00:25:22,846
[GROWLS]

369
00:25:22,933 --> 00:25:24,413
It's time
for your manicure, sir.

370
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:25,675
GOETH: Yeah, thank God.

371
00:25:29,374 --> 00:25:31,333
Your reports as requested, sir.

372
00:25:32,203 --> 00:25:33,553
[DOG GROWLS, BARKS]

373
00:25:38,035 --> 00:25:41,082
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:25:41,648 --> 00:25:42,649
[DOG GROWLS]

375
00:25:43,301 --> 00:25:45,608
[AIR RAID SIREN BLARING]

376
00:25:45,782 --> 00:25:48,089
[NEARBY EXPLOSION]
[RUMBLING]

377
00:25:48,524 --> 00:25:50,047
It's just a drill, right?

378
00:25:50,134 --> 00:25:51,440
JOSEPH: Yes, it's a test.

379
00:25:51,571 --> 00:25:53,268
It's a test to see
if a building explodes

380
00:25:53,355 --> 00:25:54,835
when you drop a missile on it.

381
00:25:54,922 --> 00:25:57,054
[NEARBY EXPLOSION]
[RUMBLING]

382
00:25:57,489 --> 00:26:00,362
[AIR-RAID SIREN
CONTINUES BLARING]

383
00:26:00,928 --> 00:26:02,103
Come on.

384
00:26:03,713 --> 00:26:05,106
Where-- where are we going?

385
00:26:05,193 --> 00:26:06,455
The closest shelter. Not far.

386
00:26:06,542 --> 00:26:08,109
Just stay calm.
[NEARBY EXPLOSION]

387
00:26:10,633 --> 00:26:13,897
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR]

388
00:26:24,168 --> 00:26:26,736
[NEARBY EXPLOSION]
[RESIDENTS SCREAM]

389
00:26:28,346 --> 00:26:30,392
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING, ECHOING]

390
00:26:34,570 --> 00:26:36,441
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

391
00:26:38,226 --> 00:26:39,270
Are you okay?

392
00:26:39,923 --> 00:26:40,924
[SIGHS]

393
00:26:44,058 --> 00:26:46,495
Sometimes I feel like my mind
can't tell the difference

394
00:26:46,582 --> 00:26:48,018
between... [SIGHS SHARPLY]

395
00:26:49,019 --> 00:26:50,978
...memories and reality.

396
00:26:51,761 --> 00:26:52,893
I know what you mean.

397
00:26:53,241 --> 00:26:55,852
The good news
is I'll die soon, so...

398
00:26:55,939 --> 00:26:57,419
[CHUCKLES]
...you know, never get old.

399
00:26:57,637 --> 00:26:59,639
You're Austrian, huh?
Yeah.

400
00:27:00,074 --> 00:27:01,989
Why does an Austrian,
such as yourself,

401
00:27:02,076 --> 00:27:03,512
care about us Jews, huh?

402
00:27:03,686 --> 00:27:04,818
[DISTANT WEAPON FIRE]

403
00:27:05,427 --> 00:27:08,604
Well, there's something
I should tell you.

404
00:27:08,691 --> 00:27:10,519
[NEARBY EXPLOSION]
[RESIDENTS SCREAM]

405
00:27:10,867 --> 00:27:12,652
[RESIDENTS CLAMORING]

406
00:27:15,219 --> 00:27:18,919
[ALARM BLARES]

407
00:27:19,093 --> 00:27:20,834
[ANNOUNCER OVER SPEAKER]
Attention, you can now exit

408
00:27:20,921 --> 00:27:22,139
the bomb shelter.

409
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:24,620
Alive?
MICHAEL: Yes, yes.

410
00:27:24,925 --> 00:27:27,144
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING IN HEBREW]

411
00:27:27,275 --> 00:27:28,537
[IN ENGLISH] Well,

412
00:27:28,668 --> 00:27:30,713
all good things
must come to an end.

413
00:27:31,322 --> 00:27:32,367
We're done here.

414
00:27:32,628 --> 00:27:35,239
But, I have more to ask--
Goodbye, Michael.

415
00:27:35,805 --> 00:27:37,633
For what it's worth, I like you.

416
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:40,723
You've got some brains
with a side of balls.

417
00:27:41,202 --> 00:27:42,377
Good luck with your case.

418
00:28:00,482 --> 00:28:01,613
[JOSEPH GROANS SOFTLY]

419
00:28:08,490 --> 00:28:09,621
[GROANS]

420
00:28:18,630 --> 00:28:22,330
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

421
00:28:39,390 --> 00:28:42,306
I want a map
of the men's barracks, 52 to 57.

422
00:28:42,959 --> 00:28:44,352
Three copies by tonight.

423
00:28:45,614 --> 00:28:48,660
Uh. But there's no sun.

424
00:28:49,270 --> 00:28:51,098
I need it for the emulsion
to harden.

425
00:28:55,015 --> 00:28:57,234
Perhaps I should find
a new mapmaker?

426
00:28:57,321 --> 00:28:58,322
JOSEPH: No. Absolutely not.

427
00:28:58,670 --> 00:29:00,411
You've already found
the finest mapmaker in the land.

428
00:29:00,542 --> 00:29:02,718
Heh, I might even make four.

429
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:04,720
Hmm. Get to it.

430
00:29:08,419 --> 00:29:09,377
[SIGHS]

431
00:29:11,031 --> 00:29:12,206
If you nick me...

432
00:29:14,077 --> 00:29:15,252
you're a dead woman.

433
00:29:17,254 --> 00:29:18,386
Yes, Kommandant.

434
00:29:20,780 --> 00:29:21,955
Slower.

435
00:29:26,568 --> 00:29:30,267
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

436
00:29:39,363 --> 00:29:40,887
JOSEPH: You're scary, huh?

437
00:29:49,112 --> 00:29:51,114
You are such a pain in my ass.

438
00:29:56,685 --> 00:30:00,820
[GRUNTS]
All right. Okay. All right.

439
00:30:06,869 --> 00:30:09,045
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

440
00:30:10,351 --> 00:30:13,484
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

441
00:30:23,190 --> 00:30:24,452
How does this work?

442
00:30:24,756 --> 00:30:27,847
Well, I am waiting
for the sunshine to come out.

443
00:30:29,239 --> 00:30:32,895
Without the sun's rays,
the emulsion won't harden.

444
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:36,899
And Goeth wants three copies
by evening, naturally.

445
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:44,472
Looks like you might
have a problem.

446
00:30:46,082 --> 00:30:48,519
Maybe you can be my sunshine?

447
00:31:09,584 --> 00:31:10,541
SOLDIER: What are you doing?

448
00:31:13,588 --> 00:31:15,111
I'm Joseph, by the way.

449
00:31:16,286 --> 00:31:19,159
Hey,
back to the woman's barracks.

450
00:31:19,550 --> 00:31:20,900
Eyes back on your work!

451
00:31:23,337 --> 00:31:24,381
Mapmaker!

452
00:31:46,664 --> 00:31:48,492
A regular Paganini.

453
00:31:49,624 --> 00:31:52,540
Okay, now I'm going
to close my eyes,

454
00:31:52,627 --> 00:31:53,933
and see the future I want.

455
00:31:55,847 --> 00:31:58,546
Oh, no. I'm only seeing black.
Okay.

456
00:32:01,505 --> 00:32:03,507
Oh, no, no, no, not the rabbit.

457
00:32:03,594 --> 00:32:06,423
I was thinking rabbi!
The spirits can't spell.

458
00:32:06,510 --> 00:32:09,905
[GROUP CHUCKLES]

459
00:32:13,735 --> 00:32:16,433
Joseph,
will you make one for me?

460
00:32:18,522 --> 00:32:20,350
Well, obviously,
you're not a Jew.

461
00:32:20,437 --> 00:32:21,612
So, what's your offense?

462
00:32:22,004 --> 00:32:23,397
Let's just say that...

463
00:32:25,007 --> 00:32:27,183
they don't approve
of who I choose to love.

464
00:32:29,229 --> 00:32:30,578
What would you like
your card to be?

465
00:32:31,231 --> 00:32:32,972
I was studying
to be an architect.

466
00:32:35,452 --> 00:32:37,280
Then an architect it is.

467
00:32:41,197 --> 00:32:44,548
[PENCIL SCRIBBLING]

468
00:32:48,596 --> 00:32:50,728
GOETH: Hmm.
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

469
00:32:50,990 --> 00:32:53,993
See what you can do
when properly incentivized?

470
00:32:54,602 --> 00:32:57,692
All it takes
is a little Aryan push.

471
00:32:57,909 --> 00:32:59,302
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

472
00:33:02,958 --> 00:33:04,394
Kommandant.
GOETH: Hmm.

473
00:33:04,742 --> 00:33:07,049
Our new mapmaker
is proving to be

474
00:33:07,180 --> 00:33:09,008
far more industrious
than the previous one.

475
00:33:09,660 --> 00:33:11,140
This Jew here...

476
00:33:13,012 --> 00:33:17,668
this Jew is far more
than just a mapmaker.

477
00:33:18,626 --> 00:33:23,196
He is also a very,
very funny fellow.

478
00:33:24,458 --> 00:33:25,589
We're done.

479
00:33:28,766 --> 00:33:29,767
Thank you, sir.

480
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:35,425
Listen to me carefully.

481
00:33:36,557 --> 00:33:40,952
That funny little Jew
is proving to be quite useful.

482
00:33:41,866 --> 00:33:44,652
So, if you intend
on disposing of him,

483
00:33:44,739 --> 00:33:47,568
you'd better have
someone equally as talented

484
00:33:47,655 --> 00:33:48,656
to replace him.

485
00:33:48,917 --> 00:33:52,355
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

486
00:33:59,145 --> 00:34:01,495
I only have a moment. [PANTS]

487
00:34:03,627 --> 00:34:05,716
I spoke with Joseph.
Good.

488
00:34:05,803 --> 00:34:09,285
[SIGHS] He worries me, Itzhak.
He's soft.

489
00:34:10,895 --> 00:34:13,550
He can do the work.
And my brother vouches for him.

490
00:34:13,724 --> 00:34:14,812
That's all I need.

491
00:34:14,899 --> 00:34:15,900
Itzhak...

492
00:34:16,684 --> 00:34:19,426
Listen to me.
Don't mistake soft for weak.

493
00:34:19,556 --> 00:34:21,471
[REBECCA SIGHS]
He's determined.

494
00:34:28,391 --> 00:34:29,784
And he's a genius.

495
00:34:32,091 --> 00:34:35,398
He's eccentric, yes,
but he's an artist.

496
00:34:35,703 --> 00:34:38,184
[SIGHS]
Don't worry about him.

497
00:34:39,228 --> 00:34:40,403
Give him a chance.

498
00:34:43,754 --> 00:34:45,800
[BELL TOLLING]

499
00:34:47,758 --> 00:34:50,239
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

500
00:34:50,500 --> 00:34:51,545
Papa.

501
00:34:51,632 --> 00:34:52,633
[COUGHING]
Hey.

502
00:34:55,157 --> 00:34:57,638
You have to eat. Come on.
[ABRAHAM GROANS]

503
00:34:58,160 --> 00:35:01,294
Come on, you stubborn ox.
Come on.

504
00:35:04,384 --> 00:35:05,385
Hey.

505
00:35:07,126 --> 00:35:08,562
I have a plan, Papa.

506
00:35:10,303 --> 00:35:12,000
There are ways
to get out of here.

507
00:35:12,087 --> 00:35:14,263
I'm going to get you,
and put you--

508
00:35:14,437 --> 00:35:16,222
[SPEAKS POLISH]

509
00:35:16,526 --> 00:35:18,224
[IN ENGLISH] Huh? No plans.

510
00:35:21,314 --> 00:35:25,100
[SNIFFS] Don't you see?
There is no leaving.

511
00:35:25,796 --> 00:35:28,190
None of us will ever escape.

512
00:35:29,539 --> 00:35:34,109
You run around here
handing out false hope,

513
00:35:34,457 --> 00:35:38,635
but the truth is,
all that is left is pain.

514
00:35:42,161 --> 00:35:44,119
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

515
00:35:44,337 --> 00:35:45,686
[GROANS]

516
00:35:46,817 --> 00:35:49,516
Life in here
is like a chess game.

517
00:35:51,082 --> 00:35:55,304
Except every move is checkmate.

518
00:36:06,228 --> 00:36:11,277
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

519
00:36:13,801 --> 00:36:15,368
[PRISONERS MUTTERING]

520
00:36:16,064 --> 00:36:19,459
SOLDIER: Line up, first row.

521
00:36:22,505 --> 00:36:24,986
[SOLDIER CONTINUES SHOUTING
IN GERMAN]

522
00:36:25,378 --> 00:36:26,379
JOSEPH: [IN ENGLISH] Papa.

523
00:36:26,466 --> 00:36:27,641
I got you.
Thank you.

524
00:36:27,771 --> 00:36:29,208
Come on.
Thank you, son.

525
00:36:30,557 --> 00:36:32,602
JOSEPH: Okay, okay.

526
00:36:32,863 --> 00:36:33,995
[ABRAHAM GROANS]

527
00:36:34,604 --> 00:36:36,867
Okay.
[PANTS, GROANS]

528
00:36:37,041 --> 00:36:39,043
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

529
00:36:39,914 --> 00:36:44,484
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

530
00:36:46,181 --> 00:36:47,443
[ABRAHAM GRUNTS FAINTLY]

531
00:36:51,447 --> 00:36:52,448
This man is done.

532
00:36:52,970 --> 00:36:55,451
No, please! He's just tired!
He's a strong man, he can work.

533
00:36:57,932 --> 00:37:00,978
Mm, the mapmaker, hmm?

534
00:37:01,588 --> 00:37:03,242
The Kommandant
was just advising me

535
00:37:03,329 --> 00:37:05,287
to take the very best
care of you.

536
00:37:07,333 --> 00:37:08,508
Your father?

537
00:37:13,121 --> 00:37:15,950
Hmm. I see the resemblance.

538
00:37:19,040 --> 00:37:20,476
Why don't you help your father

539
00:37:20,563 --> 00:37:22,348
and pull up his shirt
for me. Hmm?

540
00:37:22,435 --> 00:37:24,567
JOSEPH: No, please.
Whip me instead!

541
00:37:24,785 --> 00:37:26,090
You want me to whip you instead?

542
00:37:26,439 --> 00:37:28,789
I beg of you, please whip me!

543
00:37:29,572 --> 00:37:32,009
Well, since you insist.

544
00:37:32,140 --> 00:37:34,795
No, no. Son!

545
00:37:36,187 --> 00:37:38,799
[JOSEPH GRUNTS,
BREATHES HEAVILY]

546
00:37:38,973 --> 00:37:41,802
Don't worry, I won't touch
your precious hands.

547
00:37:43,107 --> 00:37:44,500
Count in German!

548
00:37:46,415 --> 00:37:47,460
Eins!

549
00:37:48,635 --> 00:37:49,897
Zwei!

550
00:37:50,941 --> 00:37:51,986
[WHIP CRACKING]
JOSEPH:
Drei!

551
00:37:52,073 --> 00:37:53,204
GRUEN: Again!
[WHIP CRACKING]

552
00:37:53,292 --> 00:37:54,815
[JOSEPH GROANING]
[WHIP CRACKING]

553
00:37:54,989 --> 00:37:56,817
GRUEN: Start again!
[WHIP CRACKING]

554
00:37:56,991 --> 00:38:00,168
[GRUEN GRUNTS]
[JOSEPH GROANS]

555
00:38:01,169 --> 00:38:02,475
Herr Kommandant,

556
00:38:03,606 --> 00:38:06,087
I hesitate to even mention this,
but, um...

557
00:38:06,305 --> 00:38:07,306
Yes?

558
00:38:07,741 --> 00:38:10,483
Your mapmaker is currently
being beaten out in the yard.

559
00:38:10,570 --> 00:38:13,268
And I fear we may have
some trouble finding a, uh...

560
00:38:14,269 --> 00:38:15,444
suitable replacement.

561
00:38:16,489 --> 00:38:18,926
[SCREAMS]
GRUEN: Nothing funny to say?

562
00:38:19,579 --> 00:38:21,145
Huh? Tell us a joke,
why don't you.

563
00:38:21,276 --> 00:38:23,539
[GROANS]
GRUEN: I'm sorry. What?

564
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:26,586
[LAUGHS]
[WHIP CRACKING]

565
00:38:27,587 --> 00:38:30,024
So go deal with it.
Right away, Herr Kommandant.

566
00:38:30,938 --> 00:38:31,939
Schnell!

567
00:38:32,113 --> 00:38:33,636
[ABRAHAM WAILS]

568
00:38:34,898 --> 00:38:37,336
See, you're finally starting
to make me laugh!

569
00:38:37,423 --> 00:38:39,555
[JOSEPH GROANS]

570
00:38:39,642 --> 00:38:41,862
Herr Gruen, the Kommandant

571
00:38:41,992 --> 00:38:43,124
would like to see you
immediately.

572
00:38:43,254 --> 00:38:44,517
GRUEN: Yeah, when I'm done.

573
00:38:44,647 --> 00:38:47,389
No, no! He-- he asks
that you come immediately.

574
00:38:47,737 --> 00:38:50,000
I said when I'm done!

575
00:38:50,174 --> 00:38:53,743
Of course. [BREATHES HEAVILY]
I'll notify the Kommandant.

576
00:39:00,446 --> 00:39:03,100
This isn't finished.

577
00:39:06,103 --> 00:39:08,410
[MEN CHATTERING]

578
00:39:15,548 --> 00:39:16,549
Hello?

579
00:39:20,030 --> 00:39:22,642
[JOSEPH CHUCKLES FAINTLY,
BREATHES SHAKILY]

580
00:39:24,165 --> 00:39:26,950
[GRUNTS] Thank you.
How did you...

581
00:39:27,037 --> 00:39:29,388
My sister works in
the Kommandant's kitchen.

582
00:39:31,564 --> 00:39:32,869
Oh, a chef!

583
00:39:34,828 --> 00:39:37,744
I imagine she turned down
many job offers

584
00:39:37,831 --> 00:39:40,007
at high-end,
fine dining establishments

585
00:39:40,094 --> 00:39:42,357
for this job, huh? Mm, I mean,

586
00:39:43,532 --> 00:39:45,447
who would want to work
anywhere else?

587
00:39:46,492 --> 00:39:48,319
We're also the best
to cook for, you know,

588
00:39:48,407 --> 00:39:50,931
because no matter
what you make us,

589
00:39:51,888 --> 00:39:54,630
it's always the best thing
we've ever had in our lives.

590
00:39:56,589 --> 00:39:58,199
I'm Joseph, by the way.

591
00:39:58,329 --> 00:39:59,635
Michal.
JOSEPH: Hmm.

592
00:40:00,027 --> 00:40:02,421
Nice to meet you.
Nice to meet you.

593
00:40:04,553 --> 00:40:05,554
[GRUNTS]

594
00:40:08,818 --> 00:40:10,994
[PENCIL SCRIBBLING]
[TRUCK ENGINE RUMBLING]

595
00:40:11,821 --> 00:40:13,519
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

596
00:40:18,437 --> 00:40:19,438
[BLOWS]

597
00:40:19,786 --> 00:40:21,091
[DOOR CLOSING]

598
00:40:21,222 --> 00:40:23,050
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

599
00:40:23,442 --> 00:40:24,486
MIETEK: [IN ENGLISH]
How are you?

600
00:40:26,401 --> 00:40:27,533
Not so bad.

601
00:40:28,229 --> 00:40:29,665
It only hurts when I'm awake.

602
00:40:31,537 --> 00:40:33,756
Thank you. For stopping it.

603
00:40:34,278 --> 00:40:35,802
I'm sorry it wasn't sooner.

604
00:40:36,498 --> 00:40:38,631
Um. A new shirt for you.

605
00:40:41,634 --> 00:40:45,507
It's funny,
this is all I can draw now.

606
00:40:46,943 --> 00:40:48,728
This heavenly experience.

607
00:40:49,119 --> 00:40:52,906
Yes, but-- but side-projects
like this put you in danger.

608
00:40:53,036 --> 00:40:55,952
And people are counting
on you now, to help them.

609
00:40:59,869 --> 00:41:04,395
[GROANS] You see, there are only
so many maps to be made.

610
00:41:05,658 --> 00:41:09,313
So, I mentioned
to the Kommandant,

611
00:41:09,966 --> 00:41:12,882
the deteriorating conditions
of the camp signage

612
00:41:13,579 --> 00:41:17,626
and how other camps
have much bigger, better signs.

613
00:41:18,801 --> 00:41:20,586
He ordered me straight to work.

614
00:41:24,938 --> 00:41:25,982
I, uh...

615
00:41:26,548 --> 00:41:28,855
hope you guys
aren't sick of me yet.

616
00:41:29,377 --> 00:41:31,074
Because we're back in business.

617
00:41:32,685 --> 00:41:34,208
[GROANS]
Itzhak!

618
00:41:34,425 --> 00:41:35,731
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

619
00:41:36,036 --> 00:41:39,213
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

620
00:41:42,216 --> 00:41:44,566
[WHISTLING]

621
00:41:47,787 --> 00:41:48,918
[DOG GROWLS]

622
00:41:50,659 --> 00:41:52,052
JOSEPH: [WHISPERING]
Our little secret.

623
00:41:53,314 --> 00:41:54,794
Yes.
[GROWLS SOFTLY]

624
00:41:55,664 --> 00:41:58,101
[GROWLS, BARKS]

625
00:41:58,972 --> 00:42:00,190
[BARKING]
JOSEPH: Bad dog.

626
00:42:08,242 --> 00:42:09,591
[GROWLS]

627
00:42:11,854 --> 00:42:13,116
[BARKS]

628
00:42:18,731 --> 00:42:20,994
[GROWLS, WHIMPERS]

629
00:42:26,869 --> 00:42:31,570
Ah, it's just a thank you,
for being my sunshine.

630
00:42:33,484 --> 00:42:37,576
Meshuga. [EXHALES]
That was a stupid thing to do.

631
00:42:38,402 --> 00:42:40,709
Strong words
coming from a bread thief.

632
00:42:45,453 --> 00:42:47,760
Did you know that "Rebecca"
means "captivating?"

633
00:42:48,369 --> 00:42:50,458
[SIGHS] Well, I am captive.

634
00:42:50,937 --> 00:42:53,200
You will always be
captivating to me.

635
00:42:54,244 --> 00:42:56,029
They couldn't cage you
if they tried.

636
00:42:57,204 --> 00:43:00,424
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

637
00:43:27,147 --> 00:43:29,279
[ENGINE REVVING]

638
00:43:29,497 --> 00:43:32,282
[PATRIOTIC GERMAN MUSIC PLAYING]

639
00:43:32,500 --> 00:43:33,762
ALL: Prost!

640
00:43:36,809 --> 00:43:38,419
[SMACKS LIPS]
Oskar, that's so good.

641
00:43:39,942 --> 00:43:43,467
So, you want some more
of my prisoners?

642
00:43:44,338 --> 00:43:45,382
Correct me if I am wrong,

643
00:43:45,469 --> 00:43:48,255
but are you not already
at capacity?

644
00:43:48,429 --> 00:43:50,866
I mean, how many of these people
does it take

645
00:43:50,997 --> 00:43:53,652
to make these pots and pans?

646
00:43:53,739 --> 00:43:55,610
[CHUCKLING]
You'd be surprised, Kommandant.

647
00:43:56,132 --> 00:43:59,179
This demand for new mess kits
is sky high.

648
00:43:59,266 --> 00:44:00,310
GOETH: Hmm.
Hmm.

649
00:44:00,441 --> 00:44:02,530
And we need more workers
to meet it.

650
00:44:03,226 --> 00:44:06,099
And of course,
I would remain grateful.

651
00:44:06,447 --> 00:44:07,883
[CHUCKLES, SNIFFS]

652
00:44:08,667 --> 00:44:12,453
This man loves his wine,
his woman,

653
00:44:12,671 --> 00:44:14,107
but most importantly,

654
00:44:15,325 --> 00:44:16,370
the Fatherland.

655
00:44:17,371 --> 00:44:18,720
ALL: The Fatherland!

656
00:44:21,897 --> 00:44:22,855
GOETH:
Ja.

657
00:44:23,682 --> 00:44:27,076
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

658
00:44:31,602 --> 00:44:33,039
[LAUGHTER]

659
00:44:33,343 --> 00:44:34,954
Hello.Hi.

660
00:44:36,477 --> 00:44:38,479
Don't forget your food.
Ania.

661
00:44:39,436 --> 00:44:41,438
What would my barracks
do without you?

662
00:44:42,091 --> 00:44:43,092
Thank you.

663
00:44:45,355 --> 00:44:47,706
GOETH: [SHOUTING]
Where is our food? [CHUCKLES]

664
00:44:47,836 --> 00:44:48,924
Go.

665
00:44:50,578 --> 00:44:55,278
[INDISTINCT CHATTER
AND LAUGHTER]

666
00:45:01,197 --> 00:45:03,286
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

667
00:45:04,810 --> 00:45:06,246
[YELPS]

668
00:45:06,333 --> 00:45:08,552
You burned me,
you carless bitch!

669
00:45:08,683 --> 00:45:10,032
[BOWL SHATTERING]
[CUTLERY CLATTERING]

670
00:45:11,730 --> 00:45:13,166
[BOWL SHATTERS]
[GASPS]

671
00:45:13,383 --> 00:45:15,734
I'm so sorry, sir,
I didn't mean to--

672
00:45:16,256 --> 00:45:17,387
I'll get a cloth.

673
00:45:17,605 --> 00:45:18,867
Go.
No.

674
00:45:19,128 --> 00:45:21,348
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

675
00:45:23,698 --> 00:45:25,047
[GASPS]

676
00:45:25,265 --> 00:45:27,310
My apologies about that.

677
00:45:28,529 --> 00:45:30,531
Amon, she's just a servant.

678
00:45:30,661 --> 00:45:32,663
I'm sure
she did not intend to...

679
00:45:33,186 --> 00:45:34,404
GOETH: No, no, no, Oskar,

680
00:45:34,535 --> 00:45:36,363
one only gets so many chances.

681
00:45:36,798 --> 00:45:38,147
[SCREAMS]

682
00:45:38,365 --> 00:45:39,496
[SOBBING]
[HEAVY THUD]

683
00:45:39,801 --> 00:45:40,933
Mm-hmm.

684
00:45:42,499 --> 00:45:43,936
No!
[GRUNTS]

685
00:45:44,675 --> 00:45:46,242
[HEAVY THUDS]

686
00:45:47,156 --> 00:45:49,768
[SOBS]
[HEAVY THUDS CONTINUE]

687
00:45:50,594 --> 00:45:51,595
[GRUNTS]

688
00:45:54,381 --> 00:45:57,210
[REBECCA SOBS]

689
00:45:57,950 --> 00:45:59,603
You must try the sauerkraut.

690
00:46:06,872 --> 00:46:08,090
My loyal Gruen.

691
00:46:09,657 --> 00:46:10,919
Why don't you go
clean yourself up?

692
00:46:16,185 --> 00:46:17,230
Danke.

693
00:46:19,101 --> 00:46:20,276
Oh!

694
00:46:21,364 --> 00:46:22,409
I had a thought.

695
00:46:23,018 --> 00:46:25,194
I want your opinion
on something.

696
00:46:25,934 --> 00:46:27,066
Mapmaker!

697
00:46:27,501 --> 00:46:29,242
[FINGERS SNAPPING]
Where are my posters?

698
00:46:30,417 --> 00:46:31,984
What do you think
about putting up a dozen

699
00:46:32,071 --> 00:46:33,855
of these around
your Emalia factory?

700
00:46:35,074 --> 00:46:36,205
They are very...

701
00:46:38,033 --> 00:46:39,034
striking.

702
00:46:39,382 --> 00:46:41,341
Oh, the typhus. Was my idea.

703
00:46:42,037 --> 00:46:45,388
It's a very under-reported
but significant element

704
00:46:45,475 --> 00:46:47,608
of the Jewish problem.
Hmm.

705
00:46:48,652 --> 00:46:51,264
Striking and informative. Bravo.

706
00:46:52,091 --> 00:46:56,878
I can guarantee five dozen
of these works of art

707
00:46:57,009 --> 00:46:58,619
to be exhibited at Emalia

708
00:46:58,793 --> 00:47:01,100
if you can guarantee my workers.

709
00:47:02,405 --> 00:47:05,626
Oskar,
you drive a very hard bargain.

710
00:47:05,974 --> 00:47:06,975
[CHUCKLES]

711
00:47:07,062 --> 00:47:08,759
Are you sure
you're not half Jew?

712
00:47:09,499 --> 00:47:11,110
[LAUGHS]

713
00:47:11,545 --> 00:47:13,373
Five dozen. Danke.

714
00:47:14,113 --> 00:47:15,070
Please, sit.

715
00:47:16,506 --> 00:47:18,160
OSKAR: So, the opera tonight.

716
00:47:18,334 --> 00:47:20,946
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

717
00:47:21,250 --> 00:47:23,731
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

718
00:47:23,949 --> 00:47:26,777
[WHISTLES TUNE]

719
00:47:28,083 --> 00:47:29,041
[IN ENGLISH] Hey.

720
00:47:31,608 --> 00:47:32,958
You couldn't have saved her.

721
00:47:34,481 --> 00:47:38,050
You don't know that. [GASPS]
We should have fought back.

722
00:47:38,615 --> 00:47:40,226
I should have killed that man.

723
00:47:40,356 --> 00:47:41,836
Even if you had killed him,

724
00:47:42,358 --> 00:47:44,578
you would have never made it out
of that house alive.

725
00:47:45,187 --> 00:47:47,320
I want you to live.
I need you to.

726
00:47:48,364 --> 00:47:50,714
Why? Huh?

727
00:48:04,424 --> 00:48:06,295
[BELL TOLLING]

728
00:48:08,515 --> 00:48:12,084
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]
[MAN SNORING]

729
00:48:20,919 --> 00:48:25,924
[CHANTING IN HEBREW]

730
00:48:32,452 --> 00:48:34,845
GROUP: Amen.

731
00:48:52,167 --> 00:48:54,474
[BELL TOLLING]

732
00:48:56,215 --> 00:48:59,958
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

733
00:49:04,571 --> 00:49:07,791
[SOBS]

734
00:49:19,586 --> 00:49:21,849
[WOMEN MUTTERING]

735
00:49:23,503 --> 00:49:25,113
[IN ENGLISH]
He's going to do it.

736
00:49:25,287 --> 00:49:26,985
He's got that look in his eyes.

737
00:49:30,814 --> 00:49:32,425
[SOBS]

738
00:49:37,169 --> 00:49:38,561
[SOBS]

739
00:49:38,779 --> 00:49:40,041
[REBECCA GASPS]

740
00:49:40,520 --> 00:49:42,783
[MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

741
00:49:53,446 --> 00:49:55,404
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

742
00:49:56,753 --> 00:49:58,494
[SOBS]

743
00:50:00,061 --> 00:50:03,804
[WHISTLING TUNE]

744
00:50:07,503 --> 00:50:09,549
That should do it. [GRUNTS]

745
00:50:10,071 --> 00:50:11,203
[GRUNTS]

746
00:50:11,986 --> 00:50:14,032
[SIGHS] Hey.

747
00:50:15,642 --> 00:50:18,340
Would you do me a favor
and just hold this for me?

748
00:50:19,037 --> 00:50:21,517
There we go.
Thank you. Okay.

749
00:50:22,301 --> 00:50:23,345
[WHISTLING TUNE]

750
00:50:25,391 --> 00:50:29,308
That's a good idea,
use your foot instead. There.

751
00:50:29,569 --> 00:50:30,831
What is he doing?

752
00:50:31,223 --> 00:50:33,573
JOSEPH: Thank you again
for that bread the other night.

753
00:50:37,011 --> 00:50:38,230
After the whipping...

754
00:50:39,709 --> 00:50:41,320
the pain was unbearable.

755
00:50:42,408 --> 00:50:45,498
But you know what they say,
time is the best doctor.

756
00:50:46,020 --> 00:50:48,936
Of course, I always say,
how can he be such a good doctor

757
00:50:49,023 --> 00:50:50,503
when he kills
all of his patients?

758
00:50:50,633 --> 00:50:51,678
[SOBS]

759
00:50:51,765 --> 00:50:53,158
JOSEPH:
Well, that's not entirely true,

760
00:50:53,288 --> 00:50:55,464
sometimes he tortures
and gives them diarrhea.

761
00:50:55,725 --> 00:50:58,598
Has Nazis whip our asses
into Swiss cheese.

762
00:50:59,990 --> 00:51:01,818
No laugh
at the Swiss cheese, huh?

763
00:51:04,473 --> 00:51:06,867
Oh, now I see.

764
00:51:07,607 --> 00:51:10,392
You don't want them
to waste the bullet on you.

765
00:51:11,089 --> 00:51:12,742
That's very considerate, Michal.

766
00:51:13,917 --> 00:51:17,921
They killed my sister over soup!

767
00:51:19,880 --> 00:51:20,881
I know.

768
00:51:22,317 --> 00:51:23,405
I was there.

769
00:51:24,972 --> 00:51:26,278
And I'm sorry.

770
00:51:27,496 --> 00:51:28,541
[SOBS]

771
00:51:29,716 --> 00:51:30,891
Now, imagine.

772
00:51:32,458 --> 00:51:35,852
If that fence wasn't there,
where would you go?

773
00:51:36,114 --> 00:51:37,289
What would you do?

774
00:51:37,506 --> 00:51:39,856
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

775
00:51:41,206 --> 00:51:43,556
[SNIFFLES, SOBS]
Would you be a baker?

776
00:51:44,078 --> 00:51:45,384
No!

777
00:51:45,993 --> 00:51:47,690
You give away your bread.

778
00:51:48,387 --> 00:51:50,171
[CLICKS TONGUE] You'd go broke.

779
00:51:51,259 --> 00:51:53,609
Or maybe, hmm...

780
00:51:55,698 --> 00:51:57,047
A pole vaulter?

781
00:51:57,874 --> 00:51:59,876
I don't know.
If you could do that,

782
00:52:00,007 --> 00:52:01,878
you would have cleared
the fence a long time ago.

783
00:52:03,053 --> 00:52:05,143
No.
[SOBS]

784
00:52:05,404 --> 00:52:08,233
Or maybe... [SNIFFS]
...it's something else.

785
00:52:11,279 --> 00:52:13,325
What do you want,
more than anything?

786
00:52:13,455 --> 00:52:15,022
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

787
00:52:15,544 --> 00:52:16,763
Revenge.

788
00:52:16,850 --> 00:52:18,939
JOSEPH: Wow, revenge!

789
00:52:19,983 --> 00:52:22,072
Now there's
a worthwhile pursuit.

790
00:52:22,290 --> 00:52:26,686
But... why don't we call it
justice?

791
00:52:31,430 --> 00:52:32,909
If you want justice...

792
00:52:33,954 --> 00:52:35,564
you're going to have to survive.

793
00:52:38,524 --> 00:52:40,482
And once we get out of here,

794
00:52:41,222 --> 00:52:44,573
I'll make your first
business cards free of charge.

795
00:52:44,791 --> 00:52:48,490
Although tips in bread
are always appreciated.

796
00:52:50,449 --> 00:52:52,102
Don't let them win, Michal.

797
00:52:52,842 --> 00:52:54,409
Don't let them win.

798
00:52:58,065 --> 00:52:59,240
Can I see a smile?

799
00:53:03,592 --> 00:53:04,898
There it is.

800
00:53:05,638 --> 00:53:07,161
Who is he?

801
00:53:09,555 --> 00:53:11,165
His name is Joseph.

802
00:53:14,734 --> 00:53:17,824
You are a gift from God.
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

803
00:53:18,825 --> 00:53:20,000
Nonsense.

804
00:53:20,479 --> 00:53:22,568
I am just happy to be of use.

805
00:53:22,698 --> 00:53:23,786
[WOMAN MOANS SOFTLY]

806
00:53:24,091 --> 00:53:26,485
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

807
00:53:29,270 --> 00:53:30,750
Third down, on the right.

808
00:53:31,272 --> 00:53:33,840
WOMAN: Oh, good. [MOANS SOFTLY]

809
00:53:34,667 --> 00:53:37,626
[ROMANTIC QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

810
00:53:40,934 --> 00:53:42,979
[IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
Oh, may I be next?

811
00:53:45,025 --> 00:53:46,026
[REBECCA GASPS]

812
00:53:49,029 --> 00:53:50,160
What are you doing here?

813
00:53:50,291 --> 00:53:51,858
If they catch you here,
they'll kill you.

814
00:53:51,988 --> 00:53:53,381
But I'm in disguise.

815
00:53:53,512 --> 00:53:55,165
What, you don't think
I can pass for a woman?

816
00:53:55,253 --> 00:53:56,254
Too handsome?

817
00:53:56,776 --> 00:54:00,258
[SIGHS] That is not the point.
I'm sorry, I had to see you.

818
00:54:02,782 --> 00:54:05,045
Please. I'm already here.

819
00:54:06,002 --> 00:54:08,091
Give me just five minutes,
please.

820
00:54:08,788 --> 00:54:10,833
I'll massage your feet.
[CHUCKLES]

821
00:54:11,225 --> 00:54:13,575
My feet?
Are you out of your mind?

822
00:54:14,794 --> 00:54:17,971
Yes!
[GROUP GIGGLES]

823
00:54:19,538 --> 00:54:22,280
If not for me,
then for your arches, huh?

824
00:54:28,111 --> 00:54:29,287
[SIGHS]

825
00:54:31,506 --> 00:54:32,768
Five minutes.

826
00:54:41,168 --> 00:54:42,909
We'll see how enamored
you are with me,

827
00:54:42,996 --> 00:54:44,650
after you take off my shoes.

828
00:54:49,785 --> 00:54:51,134
[JOSEPH BREATHES DEEPLY]

829
00:54:52,092 --> 00:54:54,399
This is going to take
a lot longer than five minutes.

830
00:54:54,529 --> 00:54:56,879
Oh!
No. I'm just kid-- Ah! Hey.

831
00:54:58,968 --> 00:55:00,230
They're beautiful.

832
00:55:02,494 --> 00:55:03,756
[LAUGHS]

833
00:55:04,931 --> 00:55:06,759
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

834
00:55:06,933 --> 00:55:08,413
REBECCA: You really are crazy.

835
00:55:10,502 --> 00:55:11,459
[SNIFFS]

836
00:55:14,288 --> 00:55:15,550
I saw what you did.

837
00:55:18,031 --> 00:55:19,554
You saved Michal's life.

838
00:55:21,077 --> 00:55:24,429
All I did was show
a confused boy a drawing.

839
00:55:26,822 --> 00:55:28,302
It was much more than that.

840
00:55:28,476 --> 00:55:31,349
Please, you're distracting me
from my work.

841
00:55:31,479 --> 00:55:33,525
I only have
a few minutes left, huh?

842
00:55:33,612 --> 00:55:34,700
[GIGGLES]

843
00:55:39,966 --> 00:55:41,402
Tell me your story.

844
00:55:42,751 --> 00:55:44,013
I want to know you,

845
00:55:44,579 --> 00:55:46,407
I want to know everything
about you.

846
00:55:48,583 --> 00:55:49,541
Everything?

847
00:55:51,194 --> 00:55:52,892
You only have four minutes left.

848
00:55:57,375 --> 00:55:59,246
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

849
00:56:00,247 --> 00:56:01,422
Well...

850
00:56:02,684 --> 00:56:03,642
actually...

851
00:56:04,773 --> 00:56:05,774
I'm a nurse.

852
00:56:06,862 --> 00:56:09,735
Or I was one in the ghetto.

853
00:56:11,389 --> 00:56:12,738
Now all I do is nails.

854
00:56:13,086 --> 00:56:15,610
No, you do much more than that.

855
00:56:16,002 --> 00:56:17,003
I see you.

856
00:56:18,526 --> 00:56:20,310
You take care of everybody.

857
00:56:27,840 --> 00:56:29,798
I do what I can
with what I have.

858
00:56:33,672 --> 00:56:35,369
But who takes care of you?

859
00:56:43,246 --> 00:56:44,247
Time's up.

860
00:56:49,949 --> 00:56:50,950
Next time.

861
00:56:51,646 --> 00:56:55,389
[WOMEN GIGGLE]

862
00:56:59,001 --> 00:57:02,614
[ALL LAUGH]

863
00:57:04,093 --> 00:57:06,444
[BELL TOLLING]

864
00:57:08,097 --> 00:57:11,100
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

865
00:57:15,235 --> 00:57:17,019
Mama! How are you?

866
00:57:17,455 --> 00:57:20,675
Still here. How is your father?
JOSEPH: Still Father.

867
00:57:21,328 --> 00:57:23,243
Mama, I've met a woman!

868
00:57:24,200 --> 00:57:26,159
The most wonderful woman!

869
00:57:26,246 --> 00:57:29,205
Only you, Joseph could find
something like that

870
00:57:29,292 --> 00:57:31,381
in a place like this. [CHUCKLES]

871
00:57:31,469 --> 00:57:32,513
Move it along.

872
00:57:37,039 --> 00:57:39,172
[CUTLERY CLATTERING]
JOSEPH: Hey.

873
00:57:44,656 --> 00:57:45,657
Thank you.

874
00:57:47,354 --> 00:57:48,442
For Rebecca.

875
00:57:52,141 --> 00:57:54,970
[ROMANTIC QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

876
00:57:56,450 --> 00:57:57,582
[DYTA WHISTLES]

877
00:58:10,116 --> 00:58:14,337
A date? In here? [LAUGHS]

878
00:58:15,643 --> 00:58:17,079
Are you going to go?

879
00:58:17,427 --> 00:58:21,040
[SIGHS] I don't know.
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

880
00:58:21,693 --> 00:58:24,609
I've nothing to wear.
[CHUCKLES]

881
00:58:30,092 --> 00:58:33,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

882
00:58:34,053 --> 00:58:35,358
SOLDIER: [IN GERMAN]
Inspections!

883
00:58:35,445 --> 00:58:37,578
Get away from your desks.

884
00:58:40,625 --> 00:58:41,843
[JOSEPH SIGHS]

885
00:58:45,543 --> 00:58:48,154
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

886
00:58:50,112 --> 00:58:52,506
[IN ENGLISH] Good, good, yes.
Excellent.

887
00:58:53,289 --> 00:58:54,508
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

888
00:58:55,640 --> 00:58:57,293
[ITZHAK CLEARS THROAT]
[CHUCKLES]

889
00:58:58,425 --> 00:59:00,601
Afternoon, Mietek.
Good afternoon, sir.

890
00:59:02,255 --> 00:59:04,474
Careful there. Precious cargo.

891
00:59:05,737 --> 00:59:07,390
He will be back soon.

892
00:59:09,218 --> 00:59:10,263
Itzhak.

893
00:59:10,785 --> 00:59:13,658
Oskar, have you met Mr. Bau?

894
00:59:14,572 --> 00:59:15,834
OSKAR: Not formally.

895
00:59:16,661 --> 00:59:17,966
Oskar Schindler.

896
00:59:18,793 --> 00:59:20,273
Very familiar with your work.

897
00:59:21,274 --> 00:59:24,930
Yes.
But have you seen his latest?

898
00:59:25,278 --> 00:59:26,496
Ah.

899
00:59:29,238 --> 00:59:30,283
Excellent.

900
00:59:31,893 --> 00:59:34,853
You have all the makings
of a master criminal, Mr. Bau.

901
00:59:36,811 --> 00:59:39,640
Have you heard?
They want to shut down Emalia.

902
00:59:39,771 --> 00:59:41,381
They're closing all factories

903
00:59:41,511 --> 00:59:43,122
that don't contribute
to the war effort.

904
00:59:43,209 --> 00:59:45,428
Yeah. Who needs enamelware
anyway, hmm?

905
00:59:45,559 --> 00:59:47,300
Restaurants without customers?

906
00:59:48,127 --> 00:59:50,520
Munitions,
that's where the gold is.

907
00:59:51,130 --> 00:59:54,307
A booming business.
I'm scouting in Czechoslovakia.

908
00:59:54,394 --> 00:59:55,917
[SOLDIER SPEAKING GERMAN]

909
00:59:56,048 --> 00:59:58,485
[OSKAR CLEARS THROAT, SNIFFS]

910
01:00:06,101 --> 01:00:08,060
Heil Hitler.
Heil Hitler.

911
01:00:08,495 --> 01:00:11,237
So, my friend,
what do we have today?

912
01:00:11,324 --> 01:00:12,934
OSKAR: Oh, nothing much.

913
01:00:14,283 --> 01:00:17,373
A few bottles
of Château Lafite Rothschild

914
01:00:18,374 --> 01:00:20,594
and some beluga caviar
from the Adriatic.

915
01:00:22,117 --> 01:00:25,730
My favorite, Oskar. [CHUCKLES]
You never cease to amaze me.

916
01:00:26,382 --> 01:00:28,820
Two glasses, schnell. Come.

917
01:00:34,652 --> 01:00:35,827
[DOOR CLOSES]

918
01:00:38,003 --> 01:00:41,093
Who is this Oskar Schindler?
How can you trust him?

919
01:00:41,180 --> 01:00:43,225
The man has saved
hundreds of our people.

920
01:00:43,356 --> 01:00:46,011
He's convinced the Nazis
to use us as free labor

921
01:00:46,098 --> 01:00:50,015
in his factory.
Everybody wins. Nobody dies.

922
01:00:50,406 --> 01:00:52,582
I make a list
of prisoners for Schindler.

923
01:00:52,670 --> 01:00:55,063
He asks Goeth
to re-assign them as workers.

924
01:00:55,194 --> 01:00:59,328
[SHUSHES] Let's just say,
God has given us a goy messiah.

925
01:00:59,502 --> 01:01:01,330
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]
[CORK POPS]

926
01:01:01,461 --> 01:01:03,332
JOSEPH: If Schindler
gets his workers for his factory

927
01:01:03,419 --> 01:01:04,507
with Goeth's approval,

928
01:01:04,638 --> 01:01:06,074
what's with all the forgeries
I'm creating?

929
01:01:06,161 --> 01:01:08,424
There's danger
in knowing too much.

930
01:01:08,511 --> 01:01:10,296
Oh, well, I'd hate to be
in danger.

931
01:01:10,992 --> 01:01:13,952
The Resistance
is quite creative.

932
01:01:14,517 --> 01:01:16,998
The system with Oskar
is just part of the plan.

933
01:01:17,390 --> 01:01:19,348
Weekly, Goeth signs off

934
01:01:19,435 --> 01:01:21,699
on a separate list
of prisoners to be executed.

935
01:01:22,177 --> 01:01:24,614
Our inside man
who works closely to Goeth

936
01:01:24,789 --> 01:01:26,442
provides us a copy
of this list.

937
01:01:27,052 --> 01:01:29,228
The execution list
from the inside man

938
01:01:29,315 --> 01:01:30,969
is given to Goeth's prostitute.

939
01:01:31,056 --> 01:01:32,057
WOMAN: Oh!

940
01:01:33,667 --> 01:01:35,277
MIETEK:
She gets the list
to the gardener.

941
01:01:35,800 --> 01:01:38,585
The gardener passes the list
to a Resistance member

942
01:01:38,716 --> 01:01:40,239
in the Krakow morgue.

943
01:01:41,022 --> 01:01:42,371
He then finds IDs

944
01:01:42,458 --> 01:01:45,244
from recently deceased
non-Jewish families

945
01:01:45,331 --> 01:01:47,768
that can be forged to match
the names on the list.

946
01:01:47,899 --> 01:01:51,293
He gets those IDs
back to the gardener, who then--

947
01:01:51,380 --> 01:01:53,905
Hands them to me.
I get them to you,

948
01:01:53,992 --> 01:01:55,645
and you work your magic.

949
01:01:55,733 --> 01:01:56,951
MIETEK:
And then they're smuggled out

950
01:01:57,082 --> 01:01:58,866
before they are executed.

951
01:01:59,388 --> 01:02:02,000
So, this inside man
whose copying this list

952
01:02:02,087 --> 01:02:04,480
from inside Goeth's villa
must be very good.

953
01:02:04,785 --> 01:02:05,917
She certainly is.

954
01:02:08,006 --> 01:02:09,877
Goeth keeps a copy of the list

955
01:02:10,008 --> 01:02:12,750
sitting on his desk
in the same spot every week.

956
01:02:13,359 --> 01:02:16,623
He likes to review it,
as he has his nails done.

957
01:02:18,277 --> 01:02:20,975
But-- No!
If he ever saw her doing this...

958
01:02:21,062 --> 01:02:23,761
Everyone puts their life
on the line

959
01:02:24,065 --> 01:02:26,328
for the greater cause.
[GUNSHOTS]

960
01:02:26,459 --> 01:02:28,591
It's time we go. Come.
[SOLDIER LAUGHING]

961
01:02:37,992 --> 01:02:41,082
[BELL TOLLING]

962
01:02:44,042 --> 01:02:47,001
So, tell us, what's it like
in the administration building?

963
01:02:47,088 --> 01:02:48,481
Oh, it's rough boys.

964
01:02:48,655 --> 01:02:51,527
It's not all caviar
and foie gras.

965
01:02:51,701 --> 01:02:55,140
We also have lobster pâté.
That's only on Wednesdays.

966
01:02:55,270 --> 01:02:56,619
No!
Yeah.

967
01:02:57,142 --> 01:02:59,753
Who do these sauerkraut
servants think they are, huh?

968
01:02:59,971 --> 01:03:01,450
[ALL LAUGH]
[JOSEPH GRUNTS]

969
01:03:01,537 --> 01:03:03,626
One has to watch
these Nazis like a hawk.

970
01:03:04,279 --> 01:03:05,977
I'm not sure what it is
about them yet,

971
01:03:06,064 --> 01:03:09,502
but I don't believe
they can entirely be trusted!

972
01:03:09,632 --> 01:03:13,549
[LAUGHS]
[IN GERMAN] Back to work.
Faster!

973
01:03:14,246 --> 01:03:16,248
[IN ENGLISH] You going let him
talk to you like that?

974
01:03:16,596 --> 01:03:19,555
Oh, the talking down I'm going
to give that man later.

975
01:03:19,642 --> 01:03:22,254
Nathaniel,
he's going to be so scared,

976
01:03:22,341 --> 01:03:24,082
his balls are going to be
in his throat.

977
01:03:24,169 --> 01:03:26,301
He's going to have
three Adam's apples, a bushel.

978
01:03:26,824 --> 01:03:28,608
I'll do it later in private.

979
01:03:29,435 --> 01:03:32,003
I find that when I publicly
humiliate this one,

980
01:03:32,307 --> 01:03:34,788
he starts to think
we're in a relationship.

981
01:03:35,615 --> 01:03:38,009
And I'm just not ready
for that kind of commitment.

982
01:03:38,096 --> 01:03:40,054
[ALL LAUGH]

983
01:03:40,185 --> 01:03:41,534
So, you know him, then?

984
01:03:41,926 --> 01:03:44,972
I do. [SNIFFS] He's Franz Gruen.

985
01:03:45,843 --> 01:03:47,192
You stay away from him.

986
01:03:51,805 --> 01:03:54,416
[MEN SNORING]

987
01:04:10,389 --> 01:04:11,607
[DOOR RATTLING]

988
01:04:11,956 --> 01:04:13,522
[IN GERMAN] Everybody up!
Outside! Let's go!

989
01:04:13,609 --> 01:04:14,872
[IN ENGLISH] All of you, up!

990
01:04:15,568 --> 01:04:16,525
Come on!

991
01:04:16,874 --> 01:04:20,616
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

992
01:04:21,574 --> 01:04:22,880
SOLDIER: [IN ENGLISH]
Get in there!

993
01:04:22,967 --> 01:04:26,013
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

994
01:04:29,930 --> 01:04:33,586
[PIPES RUMBLING]

995
01:04:33,934 --> 01:04:36,850
[GENTLE ORCHESTRA MUSIC PLAYING]
[OPERA SINGER SINGING IN GERMAN]

996
01:04:41,724 --> 01:04:43,030
[INAUDIBLE]

997
01:04:43,683 --> 01:04:46,425
[OPERA SINGER CONTINUES SINGING]

998
01:04:52,300 --> 01:04:54,607
[PIPES RATTLING]

999
01:04:56,565 --> 01:04:58,393
[MEN SCREAM]

1000
01:05:00,482 --> 01:05:02,354
[IN ENGLISH] You Jews,
always complaining!

1001
01:05:04,095 --> 01:05:06,619
Do your friends
find you funny now? Hot?

1002
01:05:07,359 --> 01:05:09,883
[MEN SCREAM]

1003
01:05:12,451 --> 01:05:15,715
[IN GERMAN]
Are you cold, Jew? You pigs!

1004
01:05:18,326 --> 01:05:21,068
[IN ENGLISH] Aleksy. Do you know
why they're doing this?

1005
01:05:21,460 --> 01:05:23,114
I don't think
they need a reason.

1006
01:05:23,723 --> 01:05:26,291
Next time, we'll vacation
in the tropics, okay?

1007
01:05:26,378 --> 01:05:27,945
[LAUGHS]

1008
01:05:30,773 --> 01:05:34,429
[OPERA SINGER CONTINUES SINGING]

1009
01:05:35,953 --> 01:05:39,043
I've always told you
to play by the rules,

1010
01:05:39,130 --> 01:05:41,523
but look where
this has brought us.

1011
01:05:41,915 --> 01:05:45,136
I should have seen this coming.
I should have protected you.

1012
01:05:45,223 --> 01:05:49,792
I'm your father, it's my job
to pr-- Protect you.

1013
01:05:50,010 --> 01:05:53,144
Papa, you were trying
to protect your family.

1014
01:05:53,535 --> 01:05:55,407
I am the one
who should be sorry.

1015
01:05:55,885 --> 01:05:58,062
[CONTINUES SINGING]

1016
01:06:09,247 --> 01:06:12,380
You've always played
by your own rules, Joseph.

1017
01:06:12,554 --> 01:06:16,210
And I think that has frightened
me for a long time.

1018
01:06:16,994 --> 01:06:18,778
But it doesn't anymore.

1019
01:06:20,301 --> 01:06:24,001
And I am so, so proud of you.

1020
01:06:25,306 --> 01:06:28,135
[CONTINUES SINGING]

1021
01:06:43,107 --> 01:06:45,370
[APPLAUSE]

1022
01:06:47,024 --> 01:06:48,155
Bravo!

1023
01:06:48,547 --> 01:06:51,115
[APPLAUSE CONTINUES]

1024
01:06:51,419 --> 01:06:52,855
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

1025
01:06:53,421 --> 01:06:56,555
[DOG HOWLING]

1026
01:06:57,730 --> 01:07:01,038
[AIRPLANE ENGINE RUMBLING]

1027
01:07:03,301 --> 01:07:04,998
[GUNFIRE IN DISTANCE]

1028
01:07:06,521 --> 01:07:09,176
[WHISTLES TUNE]

1029
01:07:14,268 --> 01:07:16,575
[WHISTLES TUNE]

1030
01:07:17,750 --> 01:07:20,927
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

1031
01:07:26,889 --> 01:07:29,675
I thought you'd stood me up.
I would never.

1032
01:07:29,849 --> 01:07:32,765
You were in the barracks,
the one they kept out all night.

1033
01:07:32,852 --> 01:07:34,680
I heard about it. [KISSES]
[JOSEPH SIGHS]

1034
01:07:34,767 --> 01:07:36,638
I'm sorry to postpone our date.

1035
01:07:38,075 --> 01:07:39,989
I really don't like being cold.

1036
01:07:40,512 --> 01:07:41,469
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1037
01:07:41,904 --> 01:07:45,212
You're warm now, yes?
Yeah, definitely getting warmer.

1038
01:07:45,517 --> 01:07:48,085
I should go.
JOSEPH: Wait.

1039
01:07:52,524 --> 01:07:53,786
[SIGHS]

1040
01:08:07,234 --> 01:08:09,976
ITZHAK: [CLEARS THROAT]
Joseph...

1041
01:08:10,194 --> 01:08:11,804
Do you have those maps
for the Kommandant?

1042
01:08:12,021 --> 01:08:14,589
[PANTS]

1043
01:08:14,850 --> 01:08:16,809
[PANTS]

1044
01:08:26,035 --> 01:08:28,951
[SOLDIER SPEAKING GERMAN]

1045
01:08:29,996 --> 01:08:31,867
[IN ENGLISH]
Why were you torturing
my mapmaker?

1046
01:08:32,738 --> 01:08:34,522
You forced him to stay
in the cold overnight.

1047
01:08:35,567 --> 01:08:38,657
Are you that stupid?
What if you had killed him?

1048
01:08:39,005 --> 01:08:42,226
How am I supposed to build
a work camp without maps?

1049
01:08:42,400 --> 01:08:43,488
He was disrespecting me.

1050
01:08:45,054 --> 01:08:46,665
You dare speak back to me?

1051
01:08:47,622 --> 01:08:49,276
I don't care what he was doing.

1052
01:08:50,973 --> 01:08:52,671
Don't forget your place here.

1053
01:08:53,672 --> 01:08:55,064
I picked you up
from the gutter,

1054
01:08:55,152 --> 01:08:56,588
when you were
just a lowly boxer,

1055
01:08:56,675 --> 01:08:58,155
getting beaten for a living!

1056
01:08:59,460 --> 01:09:02,376
Now, you get to do the beating.

1057
01:09:03,769 --> 01:09:05,118
When I say so.

1058
01:09:06,163 --> 01:09:07,947
Do you understand?

1059
01:09:09,731 --> 01:09:12,169
Nod, you stupid boy.

1060
01:09:13,648 --> 01:09:14,649
What's that?

1061
01:09:15,433 --> 01:09:16,477
On your cheek?

1062
01:09:18,740 --> 01:09:20,002
Are you crying?

1063
01:09:20,394 --> 01:09:22,614
[LAUGHING] Pathetic!

1064
01:09:23,310 --> 01:09:24,833
Stop crying!

1065
01:09:29,273 --> 01:09:30,404
Leave.

1066
01:09:35,496 --> 01:09:38,064
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

1067
01:09:50,381 --> 01:09:52,426
[BELL TOLLING]

1068
01:09:57,518 --> 01:09:59,694
[MEN LAUGHING]

1069
01:10:04,656 --> 01:10:08,181
Looks like you.
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1070
01:10:09,574 --> 01:10:12,316
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1071
01:10:21,325 --> 01:10:23,675
Give that to me.
ABRAHAM: No.

1072
01:10:24,415 --> 01:10:27,069
This is mine. I drew this.

1073
01:10:27,766 --> 01:10:28,810
No?

1074
01:10:29,158 --> 01:10:31,770
Herr Gruen! That's a lie,
you know this is my work.

1075
01:10:32,074 --> 01:10:34,338
A lying Jew? Hmm. [TUT-TUTS]

1076
01:10:35,774 --> 01:10:38,385
If he says it's his drawing,
then I believe him.

1077
01:10:40,039 --> 01:10:41,301
So...

1078
01:10:45,740 --> 01:10:46,872
It's your drawing?

1079
01:10:47,307 --> 01:10:48,395
ABRAHAM: Yes.

1080
01:10:48,482 --> 01:10:50,528
JOSEPH: Papa, please!
Shh.

1081
01:10:51,529 --> 01:10:52,747
You swear on it?

1082
01:10:53,400 --> 01:10:56,185
Yes, I swear on it.

1083
01:11:00,189 --> 01:11:01,190
Well...

1084
01:11:04,324 --> 01:11:05,673
I'm very sorry about this.

1085
01:11:09,198 --> 01:11:10,199
[GUN COCKING]

1086
01:11:11,592 --> 01:11:12,637
[LOUD THUD]

1087
01:11:13,638 --> 01:11:16,423
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1088
01:11:24,866 --> 01:11:28,348
Papa. [SOBS] Papa.

1089
01:11:31,699 --> 01:11:33,527
[SNIFFLES] Mama...

1090
01:11:35,181 --> 01:11:36,704
It's all my fault.

1091
01:11:37,226 --> 01:11:38,663
[SOBS]

1092
01:11:38,837 --> 01:11:42,275
The very thing he begged me
not to do over and over

1093
01:11:42,449 --> 01:11:44,669
is how I killed him.
[CYLA SOBS]

1094
01:11:44,799 --> 01:11:46,540
I never should have...

1095
01:11:46,627 --> 01:11:50,283
You know you did not do this.
You did not kill him.

1096
01:11:51,719 --> 01:11:55,201
You don't bear
any of these sins. No.

1097
01:11:55,288 --> 01:11:59,074
[SOBBING] There is no logic
in why anything happens anymore.

1098
01:11:59,597 --> 01:12:04,471
Dear, dear God,
why have you done this to us?

1099
01:12:04,558 --> 01:12:09,389
[SOBS]

1100
01:12:16,527 --> 01:12:19,181
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

1101
01:12:34,327 --> 01:12:36,155
[TRUCK ENGINE RUMBLING]

1102
01:13:12,844 --> 01:13:14,062
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1103
01:13:19,024 --> 01:13:20,939
There is something
you need to see.

1104
01:13:22,201 --> 01:13:23,245
Liquidation?

1105
01:13:23,942 --> 01:13:27,424
The entire camp.
But it is not confirmed.

1106
01:13:27,598 --> 01:13:29,904
And so far,
it's just a recommendation.

1107
01:13:30,557 --> 01:13:31,645
Oskar knows?

1108
01:13:32,559 --> 01:13:33,560
Yes.
Yeah?

1109
01:13:33,647 --> 01:13:34,692
[DOOR HANDLE RATTLING]

1110
01:13:39,305 --> 01:13:40,393
You.

1111
01:13:45,964 --> 01:13:48,793
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

1112
01:13:50,664 --> 01:13:56,322
"Making the world
a purer... place."

1113
01:14:01,240 --> 01:14:03,547
It should be race.

1114
01:14:04,330 --> 01:14:09,727
"Making the world
a purer... race"!

1115
01:14:10,641 --> 01:14:11,729
[SHOUTING] No?

1116
01:14:12,033 --> 01:14:15,297
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]
Yes, Herr.

1117
01:14:15,863 --> 01:14:19,258
You're right,
"a purer race" is much better.

1118
01:14:19,737 --> 01:14:21,042
I'll fix it immediately.

1119
01:14:21,347 --> 01:14:26,091
Did I say that you can go?

1120
01:14:26,352 --> 01:14:28,485
[CLOCK TICKING]

1121
01:14:33,968 --> 01:14:36,493
I could kill you right now,

1122
01:14:37,058 --> 01:14:39,104
sit down and finish my tea,

1123
01:14:39,931 --> 01:14:43,935
and nobody would even care.

1124
01:14:45,240 --> 01:14:46,590
The usual, Kommandant?

1125
01:14:48,722 --> 01:14:50,855
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

1126
01:14:53,640 --> 01:14:55,076
Today...

1127
01:14:56,382 --> 01:14:57,949
is your lucky day.

1128
01:14:58,123 --> 01:15:00,429
[TELEPHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

1129
01:15:03,389 --> 01:15:04,390
Out!

1130
01:15:06,392 --> 01:15:07,611
Ja,
what?

1131
01:15:08,481 --> 01:15:10,004
In two weeks, the whole camp?

1132
01:15:10,744 --> 01:15:12,659
And how do you suggest
I do that?

1133
01:15:14,400 --> 01:15:16,054
It's impossible.

1134
01:15:16,533 --> 01:15:18,665
[BELL TOLLING]

1135
01:15:20,537 --> 01:15:21,581
He's there.

1136
01:15:23,191 --> 01:15:24,323
That way.

1137
01:15:31,939 --> 01:15:35,464
I'm sorry about your father.
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

1138
01:15:35,813 --> 01:15:39,556
JOSEPH: All I can think is,
I can't lose you, too.

1139
01:15:43,951 --> 01:15:45,170
This nightmare...

1140
01:15:46,998 --> 01:15:49,957
I don't know how to stop it.
REBECCA: But you do.

1141
01:15:51,611 --> 01:15:52,612
You do.

1142
01:15:53,439 --> 01:15:54,483
You...

1143
01:15:55,223 --> 01:15:57,051
You are the magician.

1144
01:15:57,965 --> 01:15:59,184
Dream-maker.

1145
01:15:59,314 --> 01:16:01,142
The one we all look to for hope.

1146
01:16:01,229 --> 01:16:02,709
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

1147
01:16:02,840 --> 01:16:05,103
Whenever a heart has gone cold,

1148
01:16:05,190 --> 01:16:07,932
you have brought it
back to life.

1149
01:16:09,629 --> 01:16:11,022
I know because...

1150
01:16:13,285 --> 01:16:14,591
you did it for me.

1151
01:16:18,464 --> 01:16:20,335
Don't let them
take that from you.

1152
01:16:22,729 --> 01:16:25,689
What if it's already gone?

1153
01:16:25,993 --> 01:16:28,300
What if it was never
real to begin with,

1154
01:16:28,387 --> 01:16:31,346
and I was just fooling myself?

1155
01:16:31,608 --> 01:16:33,261
Well, you fooled me, too.

1156
01:16:36,874 --> 01:16:38,179
So, keep pretending.

1157
01:16:40,617 --> 01:16:44,533
In here, we are free.

1158
01:16:47,928 --> 01:16:49,147
You taught me that.

1159
01:16:53,151 --> 01:16:56,154
[GENTLE VIOLIN MUSIC PLAYING]

1160
01:16:56,284 --> 01:16:57,546
Do you hear that?

1161
01:17:04,728 --> 01:17:05,816
Are those violins?

1162
01:17:33,191 --> 01:17:34,496
Shall we dance?

1163
01:17:43,331 --> 01:17:46,247
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1164
01:18:05,527 --> 01:18:06,920
[MUSIC FADES]

1165
01:18:07,138 --> 01:18:08,966
Four? You said three!

1166
01:18:09,053 --> 01:18:11,751
No. I changed my mind.
It's now four.

1167
01:18:12,186 --> 01:18:15,581
[SIGHS] It's a good thing
I hate eating.

1168
01:18:28,072 --> 01:18:32,293
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

1169
01:18:49,223 --> 01:18:50,877
Rebecca Tennenbaum.

1170
01:18:51,922 --> 01:18:53,880
However long forever is,

1171
01:18:55,142 --> 01:18:56,535
share it with me.

1172
01:18:59,016 --> 01:19:00,931
[LAUGHS]

1173
01:19:01,409 --> 01:19:04,499
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

1174
01:19:10,027 --> 01:19:11,115
[GASPS, GIGGLES]

1175
01:19:11,898 --> 01:19:13,770
I still think
you're a crazy person.

1176
01:19:13,857 --> 01:19:15,728
Warn me if that ever changes.

1177
01:19:15,859 --> 01:19:17,121
[LAUGHS]

1178
01:19:18,513 --> 01:19:22,517
I'm afraid it's going
to be a very short engagement.

1179
01:19:23,736 --> 01:19:27,522
In fact, I have already
sent out the invitations.

1180
01:19:39,012 --> 01:19:41,667
[WOMAN SQUEALING, GIGGLING]

1181
01:19:50,589 --> 01:19:52,547
REBECCA: Cyla! [LAUGHS]
[CYLA GRUNTS SOFTLY]

1182
01:19:57,030 --> 01:19:58,205
A woman?

1183
01:19:58,336 --> 01:20:00,381
Rabbi would have
a harder time sneaking in.

1184
01:20:00,468 --> 01:20:03,471
You know,
he's not as pretty as me.
[REBECCA LAUGHS]

1185
01:20:05,386 --> 01:20:10,783
[CHANTING IN HEBREW]

1186
01:20:42,815 --> 01:20:48,690
[SPEAKING HEBREW]

1187
01:20:55,610 --> 01:20:56,611
[LAUGHS]

1188
01:20:56,698 --> 01:20:59,876
[SPEAKING HEBREW]

1189
01:21:01,181 --> 01:21:02,226
[CLEARS THROAT, SNIFFS]

1190
01:21:05,533 --> 01:21:11,409
[SPEAKING HEBREW]

1191
01:21:16,109 --> 01:21:19,112
[SPEAKING HEBREW]

1192
01:21:25,989 --> 01:21:27,338
JOSEPH: [IN ENGLISH] Okay.

1193
01:21:29,166 --> 01:21:30,297
Shh.

1194
01:21:30,732 --> 01:21:31,951
[GLASS SHATTERS]

1195
01:21:32,038 --> 01:21:34,736
[WOMEN LAUGH, CHEER]

1196
01:21:40,655 --> 01:21:44,137
[LAUGHS]

1197
01:21:44,921 --> 01:21:47,271
[EXCITED CHATTER]

1198
01:21:47,619 --> 01:21:50,274
[ALL GIGGLING]

1199
01:21:55,496 --> 01:21:56,933
ALICJA: It's a nice reminder.

1200
01:21:57,150 --> 01:21:59,500
That even in here,
you can still find love.

1201
01:21:59,674 --> 01:22:01,459
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

1202
01:22:01,763 --> 01:22:03,940
Well, maybe not you.

1203
01:22:06,029 --> 01:22:08,074
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

1204
01:22:13,645 --> 01:22:15,952
[WOMEN SNORING]

1205
01:22:21,827 --> 01:22:23,611
[ALARM BUZZING]
[WOMEN GASPING]

1206
01:22:23,698 --> 01:22:26,049
Roll call. At this hour?

1207
01:22:26,136 --> 01:22:28,616
If I'm not at line up...
Then go.

1208
01:22:28,834 --> 01:22:32,098
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR]

1209
01:22:32,490 --> 01:22:33,578
Your scarf.

1210
01:22:36,581 --> 01:22:39,714
[PANTING]

1211
01:22:43,849 --> 01:22:47,984
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

1212
01:22:49,986 --> 01:22:53,467
[DOGS BARKING]

1213
01:22:53,772 --> 01:22:56,296
[ALARM CONTINUES BUZZING]

1214
01:23:01,084 --> 01:23:03,347
[SOLDIER SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

1215
01:23:07,090 --> 01:23:10,354
[SOLDIERS SPEAKING GERMAN]

1216
01:23:10,528 --> 01:23:12,704
[SOLDIER LAUGHING]

1217
01:23:13,792 --> 01:23:15,533
[IN ENGLISH] Well?
Where are they?

1218
01:23:15,663 --> 01:23:16,795
What?

1219
01:23:16,969 --> 01:23:19,928
You have my sign posts, yes?
What sign posts?

1220
01:23:20,059 --> 01:23:21,626
Well, I've been waiting,
I was told that someone

1221
01:23:21,713 --> 01:23:23,758
was bringing me posts
to hang these signs

1222
01:23:23,845 --> 01:23:25,325
around the women's barracks.

1223
01:23:25,412 --> 01:23:26,500
What signs?

1224
01:23:26,674 --> 01:23:28,198
For the cholera outbreak.

1225
01:23:28,502 --> 01:23:32,071
The smell by the women's
latrines is truly horrifying.

1226
01:23:34,378 --> 01:23:37,555
A mass case
of explosive diarrhea, like...

1227
01:23:37,772 --> 01:23:39,731
Like a bomb went off.

1228
01:23:43,430 --> 01:23:45,911
Well, that's your job,
you handle it.

1229
01:23:46,303 --> 01:23:47,260
Go!

1230
01:23:47,347 --> 01:23:48,522
Yes, sir.
SOLDIER: Go, go, go!

1231
01:23:51,960 --> 01:23:53,310
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

1232
01:23:55,268 --> 01:23:56,965
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

1233
01:23:57,357 --> 01:23:58,576
Did you do it?

1234
01:23:59,359 --> 01:24:03,102
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1235
01:24:03,929 --> 01:24:06,149
A wedding? I can't believe it!

1236
01:24:14,592 --> 01:24:16,333
JOSEPH: Itzhak! Hey.

1237
01:24:18,509 --> 01:24:21,773
Eh, so, what's next?
More IDs?

1238
01:24:21,860 --> 01:24:24,036
I'm afraid the time
for that is over.

1239
01:24:24,123 --> 01:24:27,126
What's happening?
ITZHAK: The liquidation
is to proceed.

1240
01:24:27,257 --> 01:24:29,085
Mietek has seen memos
to confirm.

1241
01:24:30,173 --> 01:24:32,349
They plan to leave
no trace for the Russians.

1242
01:24:32,610 --> 01:24:35,178
[SIGHS]
What does that mean for us?

1243
01:24:36,092 --> 01:24:37,441
Extermination.

1244
01:24:39,530 --> 01:24:41,923
Most of us are being sent
to Auschwitz almost immediately.

1245
01:24:42,010 --> 01:24:44,274
The lucky ones
will go with Schindler

1246
01:24:44,361 --> 01:24:45,449
to his factory in Brünnlitz.

1247
01:24:45,536 --> 01:24:47,059
There must be more
that we can do.

1248
01:24:47,146 --> 01:24:48,191
There must!

1249
01:24:48,756 --> 01:24:50,715
Let's think about that once
you get to Schindler's factory.

1250
01:24:50,845 --> 01:24:53,370
Rebecca, she has to get
sent to the factory.

1251
01:24:53,457 --> 01:24:55,111
We have to get her on that list.

1252
01:24:55,676 --> 01:24:57,591
And my mother.
I cannot.

1253
01:24:58,244 --> 01:25:01,204
I can't add any more names.
The total number is final.

1254
01:25:03,380 --> 01:25:04,337
I'm sorry.

1255
01:25:04,903 --> 01:25:08,167
[PANTS, HESITATES] Itzhak!

1256
01:25:08,559 --> 01:25:10,474
Then let me
take their place for them.

1257
01:25:10,561 --> 01:25:12,258
Take them instead of me.

1258
01:25:12,432 --> 01:25:14,608
I'll be your inside man
at Auschwitz.

1259
01:25:14,739 --> 01:25:17,133
Please! Help them.

1260
01:25:17,350 --> 01:25:19,483
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

1261
01:25:20,571 --> 01:25:21,963
I will see what I can do.

1262
01:25:25,315 --> 01:25:27,055
And Joseph, uh...

1263
01:25:28,622 --> 01:25:30,233
mazel tov on your wedding.

1264
01:25:30,755 --> 01:25:31,669
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1265
01:25:31,973 --> 01:25:33,845
We don't encounter
much good news around here,

1266
01:25:33,975 --> 01:25:37,849
so when we do, it's...
it gets around quick.

1267
01:25:38,023 --> 01:25:40,417
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

1268
01:25:40,504 --> 01:25:42,810
[FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING]
[DOOR OPENING]

1269
01:25:50,340 --> 01:25:52,820
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

1270
01:26:08,445 --> 01:26:10,098
What do you think you're doing?

1271
01:26:10,795 --> 01:26:13,276
I'm only setting up, Kommandant.

1272
01:26:13,667 --> 01:26:16,409
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]
[GASPS, BREATHES HEAVILY]

1273
01:26:17,149 --> 01:26:22,894
You think I don't see you
always looking around?

1274
01:26:24,417 --> 01:26:30,031
Everywhere, like a little rat
looking for some cheese.

1275
01:26:32,164 --> 01:26:35,385
Perhaps you found some?
[WHIMPERS]

1276
01:26:36,081 --> 01:26:37,430
Do you know what this is?

1277
01:26:39,345 --> 01:26:40,520
[SHOUTING] Do you?

1278
01:26:41,217 --> 01:26:42,218
No.
No.

1279
01:26:43,915 --> 01:26:47,527
These people will be sent
to a factory,

1280
01:26:48,485 --> 01:26:50,226
where they will work
for the Reich.

1281
01:26:51,444 --> 01:26:55,274
[LAUGHS]
You should be happy for them.

1282
01:26:58,234 --> 01:27:02,020
Why are you looking
at this list?

1283
01:27:02,281 --> 01:27:05,589
No reason, Kommandant.
My eyes just fell on it.

1284
01:27:05,850 --> 01:27:07,373
I meant no harm.

1285
01:27:08,374 --> 01:27:09,810
Traitor!
[SCREAMS]

1286
01:27:13,249 --> 01:27:16,252
You Jews are all the same.

1287
01:27:16,991 --> 01:27:19,907
So scared all the time.

1288
01:27:20,081 --> 01:27:21,909
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

1289
01:27:22,214 --> 01:27:26,131
But you are not
my problem anymore!

1290
01:27:33,399 --> 01:27:34,705
[SHOUTING] Get out!
[YELPS]

1291
01:27:43,366 --> 01:27:44,410
[DOOR CLOSING]

1292
01:27:47,805 --> 01:27:50,590
Joseph isn't here.
I came to speak with you.

1293
01:27:53,376 --> 01:27:55,029
Why is my name
on Schindler's list

1294
01:27:55,116 --> 01:27:56,292
and not Joseph's?

1295
01:28:00,034 --> 01:28:02,776
He made you change it.
To save me.

1296
01:28:06,563 --> 01:28:07,564
Change it back.

1297
01:28:08,304 --> 01:28:10,088
ITZHAK: Rebecca, please--
You have to, Itzhak.
And you know it.

1298
01:28:11,219 --> 01:28:13,874
He's far more valuable
to the Resistance than I am.

1299
01:28:13,961 --> 01:28:15,311
Look, I don't want--

1300
01:28:15,398 --> 01:28:18,270
He will be angry with you,
worried for me.

1301
01:28:19,358 --> 01:28:20,403
But that means nothing

1302
01:28:20,577 --> 01:28:22,927
next to the hundreds
of people he can help.

1303
01:28:24,755 --> 01:28:28,367
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1304
01:28:31,892 --> 01:28:34,025
That is our mission.

1305
01:28:35,809 --> 01:28:37,245
Not to save one life.

1306
01:28:38,464 --> 01:28:41,119
To save hundreds. Thousands.

1307
01:28:46,167 --> 01:28:47,560
I'm a survivor.

1308
01:28:49,345 --> 01:28:50,433
I'll find a way.

1309
01:28:56,613 --> 01:28:57,744
[SNIFFLING]

1310
01:28:58,789 --> 01:29:00,094
[SIGHS]

1311
01:29:00,443 --> 01:29:01,835
Take care of him for me.

1312
01:29:08,364 --> 01:29:09,365
Tell him nothing.

1313
01:29:20,114 --> 01:29:21,899
[EXPLOSIONS]

1314
01:29:21,986 --> 01:29:24,075
[BOMB WHISTLING]
[GUNFIRE]

1315
01:29:24,205 --> 01:29:26,730
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
[EXPLOSION]

1316
01:29:28,296 --> 01:29:30,124
SOLDIER:
[OVER SPEAKER, IN GERMAN]
All prisoners report

1317
01:29:30,211 --> 01:29:31,561
to the train platform
immediately.

1318
01:29:32,431 --> 01:29:34,955
Ah, don't you look pretty?

1319
01:29:35,478 --> 01:29:38,698
[SOLDIERS SPEAKING GERMAN,
LAUGHING]

1320
01:29:39,264 --> 01:29:40,396
[SOLDIER GRUNTS]

1321
01:29:40,570 --> 01:29:42,659
[DOG BARKING]
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR]

1322
01:29:43,050 --> 01:29:44,400
[GROANS]

1323
01:29:47,968 --> 01:29:51,145
SOLDIER: [OVER SPEAKER]
Passengers to Auschwitz,
go to platform four.

1324
01:29:51,450 --> 01:29:53,757
All other passengers
go to platform three.

1325
01:29:54,975 --> 01:29:55,933
[IN ENGLISH] Out!

1326
01:29:57,761 --> 01:30:00,546
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

1327
01:30:02,461 --> 01:30:05,421
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

1328
01:30:07,640 --> 01:30:10,687
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1329
01:30:14,604 --> 01:30:18,956
[WHISTLES TUNE]

1330
01:30:21,175 --> 01:30:23,395
[WHISTLES TUNE]

1331
01:30:23,787 --> 01:30:24,875
Rebecca.

1332
01:30:26,398 --> 01:30:28,400
Joseph? Joseph...

1333
01:30:30,663 --> 01:30:32,317
Joseph.
JOSEPH: Rebecca.

1334
01:30:35,276 --> 01:30:38,236
[SOBS] Joseph.

1335
01:30:39,063 --> 01:30:40,412
JOSEPH: [IN ENGLISH] My love.

1336
01:30:41,805 --> 01:30:44,895
I'll be okay, I promise.
I wrote this for you.

1337
01:30:45,896 --> 01:30:47,898
I'll find you. No matter what.

1338
01:30:48,028 --> 01:30:50,204
I love you.
I love you.

1339
01:30:50,335 --> 01:30:51,858
This one is mine.

1340
01:30:53,251 --> 01:30:54,731
Where did you think
you were going?

1341
01:30:54,948 --> 01:30:57,255
I love you!
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1342
01:30:57,516 --> 01:30:58,561
Let's go.

1343
01:30:58,691 --> 01:31:00,911
I specifically asked
the Kommandant

1344
01:31:00,998 --> 01:31:02,782
to let me give you
a special goodbye.

1345
01:31:03,391 --> 01:31:04,349
He forbid it.

1346
01:31:05,089 --> 01:31:06,830
Now he is not here
to stop me, is he?

1347
01:31:06,917 --> 01:31:08,701
[ITZHAK SHOUTING]

1348
01:31:08,788 --> 01:31:11,138
This one is on the list
for Schindler's factory.

1349
01:31:11,878 --> 01:31:12,966
What is that?

1350
01:31:13,619 --> 01:31:14,838
Give that to me.

1351
01:31:15,099 --> 01:31:18,189
You've made a mistake!
Take her instead of me.

1352
01:31:19,277 --> 01:31:20,452
Rebecca!

1353
01:31:20,539 --> 01:31:21,714
ITZHAK: This is what she wanted!

1354
01:31:23,629 --> 01:31:26,458
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR]
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

1355
01:31:31,811 --> 01:31:34,510
[INDISTINCT CLAMOR CONTINUES]

1356
01:31:36,816 --> 01:31:38,296
[SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

1357
01:31:53,398 --> 01:31:55,008
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

1358
01:31:55,182 --> 01:31:59,273
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1359
01:32:08,369 --> 01:32:10,633
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

1360
01:32:39,662 --> 01:32:42,360
JOSEPH: [IN ENGLISH]
I measured your figure
with my own,

1361
01:32:42,708 --> 01:32:46,190
counted your eyelashes
with the tip of my tongue.

1362
01:32:46,799 --> 01:32:48,366
And hungering for you,

1363
01:32:48,888 --> 01:32:51,369
recited your virtues
from memory.

1364
01:32:51,804 --> 01:32:54,851
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

1365
01:33:01,335 --> 01:33:06,950
[CLOCK BELL DINGING]

1366
01:33:19,092 --> 01:33:22,052
[TRAFFIC RUMBLING]

1367
01:33:28,101 --> 01:33:30,408
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

1368
01:33:31,322 --> 01:33:34,368
[SEAGULL SQUAWKING]

1369
01:33:34,978 --> 01:33:40,287
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1370
01:33:50,080 --> 01:33:51,472
SAUL: Good to see you,
my friend.

1371
01:33:51,603 --> 01:33:53,605
JOSEPH: Ah.
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1372
01:33:54,562 --> 01:33:56,521
SAUL: Please.
[JOSEPH GROANS]

1373
01:33:57,130 --> 01:33:59,089
SAUL: Well,
did you bring me anything?

1374
01:33:59,350 --> 01:34:00,743
[SIGHS]

1375
01:34:13,799 --> 01:34:15,018
Great.

1376
01:34:15,932 --> 01:34:18,499
This should see our friends
safely into Argentina.

1377
01:34:19,849 --> 01:34:21,198
And the Russian ones?

1378
01:34:22,329 --> 01:34:25,376
They're coming. I'm...
I'm sorry, I just...

1379
01:34:26,116 --> 01:34:28,031
I've had a lot
on my mind lately.

1380
01:34:28,988 --> 01:34:30,598
Anything you'd like
to talk about?

1381
01:34:31,164 --> 01:34:34,298
Uh... I'm fine.

1382
01:34:39,869 --> 01:34:44,264
You know, Joseph, I may come
across as an ungrateful sod,

1383
01:34:45,004 --> 01:34:48,355
but the agency values you
and your work immensely.

1384
01:34:49,966 --> 01:34:53,143
So, have you decided
if you're going to testify?

1385
01:34:57,016 --> 01:34:58,714
Nothing gets past the Mossad.

1386
01:35:00,977 --> 01:35:02,326
Testify, you mean...

1387
01:35:02,456 --> 01:35:03,936
What's the good in this, huh?

1388
01:35:04,023 --> 01:35:06,591
I mean, it's not going
to bring anybody back.

1389
01:35:06,678 --> 01:35:10,682
It's not about going back,
it's about moving forward.

1390
01:35:15,948 --> 01:35:19,386
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

1391
01:35:19,691 --> 01:35:22,085
[JET ENGINES ROARING]

1392
01:35:26,132 --> 01:35:28,178
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

1393
01:35:40,538 --> 01:35:44,281
[MACHINERY WHIRRING]

1394
01:35:44,498 --> 01:35:46,065
[MUSIC FADES]

1395
01:35:47,066 --> 01:35:49,634
[MACHINERY CREAKING]

1396
01:35:59,557 --> 01:36:00,645
OSKAR: Joseph.

1397
01:36:00,950 --> 01:36:02,778
When will the next set
of documents be ready?

1398
01:36:02,952 --> 01:36:04,127
Oskar.

1399
01:36:04,823 --> 01:36:06,520
What is happening at Auschwitz?

1400
01:36:07,391 --> 01:36:09,915
[HESITATES]
Nothing is confirmed.

1401
01:36:10,089 --> 01:36:14,180
All I know is that
the Allies are gaining ground,

1402
01:36:14,833 --> 01:36:16,835
and the Reich continues
to demand all evidence

1403
01:36:16,922 --> 01:36:18,750
of the camps be destroyed.

1404
01:36:31,197 --> 01:36:32,416
They hung Goeth.

1405
01:36:32,720 --> 01:36:34,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

1406
01:36:35,941 --> 01:36:37,987
[ECHOING THUD]
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

1407
01:36:39,379 --> 01:36:40,467
[OSKAR EXHALES]

1408
01:36:40,816 --> 01:36:43,644
The Nazis found a warehouse full
of prisoner property.

1409
01:36:44,341 --> 01:36:46,604
Never a good idea to steal
from the Reich.

1410
01:36:48,084 --> 01:36:50,434
But what have you heard
about Auschwitz?

1411
01:36:50,695 --> 01:36:52,349
There must be survivors, right?

1412
01:36:52,653 --> 01:36:56,266
Very little from Auschwitz
has ever been reported.

1413
01:36:56,570 --> 01:36:58,137
But what is that little?

1414
01:36:58,659 --> 01:37:00,183
You're asking a question

1415
01:37:00,357 --> 01:37:02,011
to which you already
know the answer.

1416
01:37:07,538 --> 01:37:08,974
They're just rumors.

1417
01:37:16,677 --> 01:37:17,940
[SIGHS]

1418
01:37:21,465 --> 01:37:24,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

1419
01:37:24,424 --> 01:37:28,820
An old friend...
from Goeth's warehouse.

1420
01:37:32,041 --> 01:37:33,346
GRUEN: Give that to me!

1421
01:37:34,130 --> 01:37:37,829
Never give up.
Miracles do happen.

1422
01:38:00,896 --> 01:38:01,984
[ALARM BUZZES]

1423
01:38:02,245 --> 01:38:04,029
SOLDIER:
[OVER SPEAKER, IN GERMAN]
Attention!

1424
01:38:04,160 --> 01:38:07,511
All prisoners report
to Schindler's factory.

1425
01:38:08,338 --> 01:38:11,123
[ALARM CONTINUES BUZZING]
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1426
01:38:13,169 --> 01:38:18,739
[SOLDIER CONTINUES MAKING
ANNOUNCEMENT OVER SPEAKER]

1427
01:38:21,394 --> 01:38:23,440
MIETEK: [IN ENGLISH]
Psst, psst, Itzhak, Joseph.

1428
01:38:25,268 --> 01:38:28,793
Germany has surrendered!
The war is over?

1429
01:38:28,967 --> 01:38:31,013
What... what does that mean?

1430
01:38:33,102 --> 01:38:34,364
It means we survived.

1431
01:38:34,799 --> 01:38:36,975
The Fatherland has surrendered.

1432
01:38:37,933 --> 01:38:39,412
This telegram confirms it.

1433
01:38:39,630 --> 01:38:42,546
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

1434
01:38:42,938 --> 01:38:45,941
There's no reason for you
to die in a Russian prison camp

1435
01:38:46,680 --> 01:38:49,161
or to be tortured to suffer
an agonizing death?

1436
01:38:49,248 --> 01:38:51,250
No, your best bet
is to flee, quickly.

1437
01:38:51,642 --> 01:38:54,166
Go! Don't worry,
I won't report you for running,

1438
01:38:54,253 --> 01:38:56,560
you can count on that. Go.

1439
01:39:03,088 --> 01:39:04,263
The rest of the telegram

1440
01:39:04,611 --> 01:39:07,223
instructed him to exterminate
all the Jews in this building.

1441
01:39:08,441 --> 01:39:11,270
What a pity they left
before I could finish.

1442
01:39:11,967 --> 01:39:13,794
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

1443
01:39:14,143 --> 01:39:16,884
[PRISONERS CHEERING, LAUGHING]

1444
01:39:17,015 --> 01:39:19,670
Oskar. What will you do?

1445
01:39:19,844 --> 01:39:22,151
I'll have to flee, too,
of course.

1446
01:39:23,935 --> 01:39:25,632
But this moment isn't about me.

1447
01:39:27,460 --> 01:39:30,115
Now, is a time for celebration.

1448
01:39:30,507 --> 01:39:31,551
[CHUCKLES]

1449
01:39:31,812 --> 01:39:35,207
To freedom.
To freedom.

1450
01:39:36,078 --> 01:39:37,166
[CORK POPS]

1451
01:39:37,383 --> 01:39:39,429
[PRISONERS LAUGHING, CHEERING]
OSKAR: To freedom!

1452
01:39:41,953 --> 01:39:44,434
So... we can go?

1453
01:39:44,738 --> 01:39:46,740
Just like that?
Yes.

1454
01:39:47,741 --> 01:39:51,571
We're free to go, Joseph.
We can do as we please.

1455
01:39:53,182 --> 01:39:56,489
Well, then I must see you later,
dear friends.

1456
01:40:00,058 --> 01:40:01,407
[CHUCKLES]

1457
01:40:08,675 --> 01:40:09,807
[TRAIN CHUGGING]

1458
01:40:15,552 --> 01:40:19,382
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]
[DRAMATIC SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1459
01:41:02,425 --> 01:41:05,123
[TELEPHONE RINGING]
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1460
01:41:30,322 --> 01:41:31,671
WORKER: Who are you looking for?

1461
01:41:31,758 --> 01:41:34,413
Um, an Auschwitz survivor.
Tennenbaum.

1462
01:41:34,500 --> 01:41:37,242
Rebecca Tennenbaum.
Maybe Rebecca Bau.

1463
01:41:41,681 --> 01:41:43,727
Are you certain
she was sent to Auschwitz?

1464
01:41:43,814 --> 01:41:47,034
Uh, in '44.
I don't know the month.

1465
01:41:47,470 --> 01:41:49,515
There is no record of her.
JOSEPH: Are you sure?

1466
01:41:49,733 --> 01:41:51,038
For either name.

1467
01:41:52,039 --> 01:41:53,215
I'm sorry.

1468
01:42:05,140 --> 01:42:06,271
DYTA: Joseph?

1469
01:42:08,404 --> 01:42:11,537
Dyta! [CHUCKLES]
[DYTA CHUCKLES]

1470
01:42:13,757 --> 01:42:14,975
Where is she?

1471
01:42:16,063 --> 01:42:20,764
Uh, um, before the camps
were liberated,

1472
01:42:20,851 --> 01:42:26,030
a... a number of us were moved
from Auschwitz to Lichtewerden.

1473
01:42:27,249 --> 01:42:30,034
The Nazis were trying to stay
ahead of the Allies. But...

1474
01:42:31,078 --> 01:42:35,953
eventually, they got too close
and... most of the Nazis fled.

1475
01:42:36,562 --> 01:42:41,698
Rebecca and I escaped,
on a wagon outside Silesia.

1476
01:42:42,612 --> 01:42:44,918
But... uh...

1477
01:42:46,050 --> 01:42:47,791
Th... There was an accident.

1478
01:42:49,662 --> 01:42:51,229
The wagon flipped.

1479
01:42:51,360 --> 01:42:52,317
[SIGHS]

1480
01:42:52,404 --> 01:42:54,972
And... I was thrown clear but...

1481
01:42:56,365 --> 01:43:01,152
Rebecca, she, uh...
was trapped underneath, and...

1482
01:43:01,892 --> 01:43:05,243
I ran for help,
but it was so dark,

1483
01:43:05,330 --> 01:43:08,420
and I couldn't find
my way back to her.

1484
01:43:09,726 --> 01:43:11,815
I just left her there.

1485
01:43:11,989 --> 01:43:14,731
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1486
01:43:14,861 --> 01:43:18,778
I am so sorry, Joseph.
I am so sorry!

1487
01:43:20,040 --> 01:43:21,216
And my mother?

1488
01:43:25,524 --> 01:43:26,612
I'm sorry.

1489
01:43:34,533 --> 01:43:38,015
JOSEPH: I'll keep looking
for Rebecca, no matter what.

1490
01:43:38,145 --> 01:43:41,410
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1491
01:43:51,855 --> 01:43:54,249
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

1492
01:44:06,739 --> 01:44:08,306
JOSEPH: Rebecca,
Rebecca Tennenbaum.

1493
01:44:08,524 --> 01:44:10,090
No.
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1494
01:44:10,221 --> 01:44:11,483
Try upstairs.

1495
01:44:12,397 --> 01:44:13,659
[SHOUTING] Rebecca?

1496
01:44:14,704 --> 01:44:16,401
Rebecca Tennenbaum?

1497
01:44:17,359 --> 01:44:18,925
Rebecca Bau?

1498
01:44:19,404 --> 01:44:21,058
Rebecca Tennenbaum?

1499
01:44:41,208 --> 01:44:42,340
Rebecca.

1500
01:44:43,733 --> 01:44:45,735
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

1501
01:44:59,792 --> 01:45:05,015
GRUEN:
This Jew is far more
than just a mapmaker.

1502
01:45:05,320 --> 01:45:07,365
This one is mine!
JOSEPH: Rebecca!

1503
01:45:26,906 --> 01:45:29,256
[BELL TOLLING]

1504
01:45:34,653 --> 01:45:35,741
KARL: Mr. Bau.

1505
01:45:36,873 --> 01:45:38,396
I'm Karl Richter.

1506
01:45:39,005 --> 01:45:40,964
I am lead counsel
for the defendant.

1507
01:45:42,095 --> 01:45:45,751
I would like to say, that I am
an admirer of your work.

1508
01:45:47,362 --> 01:45:51,017
And that I'm sorry
for your loss during the war.

1509
01:45:52,802 --> 01:45:53,803
Losses.

1510
01:45:56,283 --> 01:45:57,415
I see the anger.

1511
01:45:58,460 --> 01:46:01,201
There is no reason
to direct this at me.

1512
01:46:02,028 --> 01:46:05,641
Don't you believe every accused
party deserves a defense?

1513
01:46:07,382 --> 01:46:10,341
Go to Plaszow prison camp
in 1943

1514
01:46:10,428 --> 01:46:12,082
and ask the same question.

1515
01:46:16,086 --> 01:46:18,436
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]
[ECHOING THUDS]

1516
01:46:29,534 --> 01:46:31,536
GRUEN: [ECHOING]
Nothing funny to say?

1517
01:46:40,589 --> 01:46:42,286
GRUEN:
I said start again!

1518
01:46:42,417 --> 01:46:44,244
[WHIP CRACKING]
[JOSEPH GROANING, ECHOING]

1519
01:46:49,902 --> 01:46:50,947
Herr Richter.

1520
01:46:51,730 --> 01:46:53,079
[MUSIC FADES]

1521
01:46:53,297 --> 01:46:54,951
Enjoying a chat with my witness?

1522
01:46:55,386 --> 01:46:57,040
Hardly a chat, Counselor.

1523
01:46:57,954 --> 01:46:59,172
Only a courtesy.

1524
01:47:01,174 --> 01:47:02,437
See you on the stand.

1525
01:47:04,569 --> 01:47:07,529
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

1526
01:47:15,667 --> 01:47:16,929
Would you like
to run through anything?

1527
01:47:17,016 --> 01:47:18,061
No.

1528
01:47:19,541 --> 01:47:21,847
No run-throughs. [GROANS]

1529
01:47:22,152 --> 01:47:26,112
No practices, no advice.
No encouragement.

1530
01:47:27,244 --> 01:47:30,726
I will say what I will say.
And that will be that.

1531
01:47:32,205 --> 01:47:33,598
MICHAEL:
You know, there's

1532
01:47:34,338 --> 01:47:36,775
something I've been meaning
to say to you.

1533
01:47:41,432 --> 01:47:44,914
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

1534
01:47:53,444 --> 01:47:54,706
Justice.

1535
01:47:55,490 --> 01:47:57,143
You're not here because of me.

1536
01:47:58,405 --> 01:48:00,843
I'm here because of you.

1537
01:48:02,322 --> 01:48:03,628
Michal?

1538
01:48:04,324 --> 01:48:05,717
[CHUCKLES]

1539
01:48:08,067 --> 01:48:09,329
You gave me a future.

1540
01:48:09,939 --> 01:48:10,940
JOSEPH: No.

1541
01:48:11,593 --> 01:48:13,943
I merely reminded you
it was there.

1542
01:48:14,117 --> 01:48:16,902
[CHUCKLES]
Wow.

1543
01:48:19,949 --> 01:48:21,211
To justice.

1544
01:48:24,519 --> 01:48:26,129
Now, let's show some balls.

1545
01:48:35,312 --> 01:48:38,184
[MUSIC FADES]

1546
01:48:38,315 --> 01:48:41,623
KARL: So, you didn't actually
see the defendant

1547
01:48:41,840 --> 01:48:43,538
strike Ania Wancowski.

1548
01:48:44,364 --> 01:48:46,018
I heard him beat her to death.

1549
01:48:47,063 --> 01:48:48,760
KARL: But you didn't
see it happen.

1550
01:48:49,631 --> 01:48:52,764
[ANIA SCREAMING, ECHOING]
The sounds were horrible.

1551
01:48:54,200 --> 01:48:55,375
Unmistakable.

1552
01:48:56,376 --> 01:48:58,291
[ANIA CONTINUES SCREAMING]

1553
01:48:58,988 --> 01:49:01,381
Do you know of anyone else
who might have seen it happen?

1554
01:49:01,468 --> 01:49:04,515
I was right there.
I know what happened.

1555
01:49:04,602 --> 01:49:07,736
KARL: And yet
you didn't see anything.

1556
01:49:08,867 --> 01:49:13,611
Is it not possible,
that your traumatic experiences

1557
01:49:13,959 --> 01:49:15,265
in the camp...

1558
01:49:16,092 --> 01:49:18,224
of which I'm sure
there were many,

1559
01:49:19,399 --> 01:49:24,404
has left your memories
a bit unreliable?

1560
01:49:25,623 --> 01:49:29,061
[HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

1561
01:49:31,629 --> 01:49:34,327
Is it not the case
that certain medical records

1562
01:49:34,414 --> 01:49:38,375
state that you suffer
from shell shock.

1563
01:49:38,462 --> 01:49:39,985
[WHIP CRACKING]
[GROANS]

1564
01:49:40,246 --> 01:49:42,553
KARL: [ECHOING]
A form of mental illness?

1565
01:49:47,863 --> 01:49:50,169
[EERIE SCREECH]

1566
01:49:50,256 --> 01:49:52,432
GOETH: [ECHOING]
I could kill you, right now,

1567
01:49:52,519 --> 01:49:56,828
and nobody would even care.

1568
01:49:57,829 --> 01:49:58,874
[ECHOING EXPLOSION]

1569
01:49:59,309 --> 01:50:02,834
KARL: You don't think that
affects your memory at all?

1570
01:50:03,835 --> 01:50:05,271
You are the magician.

1571
01:50:06,272 --> 01:50:08,448
In here, we are free.

1572
01:50:09,536 --> 01:50:11,538
Don't let them
take that from you.

1573
01:50:12,278 --> 01:50:16,935
I know this is difficult,
Mr. Bau, to revisit the losses

1574
01:50:17,022 --> 01:50:19,111
you suffered in the war.

1575
01:50:19,982 --> 01:50:24,290
I can imagine
the trauma that comes

1576
01:50:24,421 --> 01:50:26,553
with losing
a close family member.

1577
01:50:26,641 --> 01:50:28,991
How that... disturbs the mind.

1578
01:50:29,121 --> 01:50:30,993
Objection. Is...
is there a question here?

1579
01:50:31,080 --> 01:50:32,908
Get to the point,
Herr Richter.

1580
01:50:33,865 --> 01:50:34,910
Mr. Bau.

1581
01:50:35,562 --> 01:50:39,436
To your knowledge,
did your counsel suffer the loss

1582
01:50:39,523 --> 01:50:41,220
of a family
member during the war?

1583
01:50:44,354 --> 01:50:47,487
Yes. His sister.

1584
01:50:48,358 --> 01:50:49,794
Ania Wancowski.

1585
01:50:50,055 --> 01:50:53,929
The victim who you accused
my client of murdering.

1586
01:50:55,974 --> 01:50:57,846
So much loss.

1587
01:50:59,412 --> 01:51:02,198
So much suffering.

1588
01:51:03,547 --> 01:51:08,508
And only one Nazi official here

1589
01:51:08,770 --> 01:51:10,075
to blame.

1590
01:51:12,338 --> 01:51:15,646
Is it not natural instinct,
Mr. Bau,

1591
01:51:15,777 --> 01:51:18,170
to place your rage on him?

1592
01:51:19,041 --> 01:51:20,085
Well...

1593
01:51:21,086 --> 01:51:22,653
he has earned it.
[CHUCKLES]

1594
01:51:22,740 --> 01:51:25,047
KARL: You believe
the defendant is guilty

1595
01:51:25,134 --> 01:51:26,918
of horrible, repeatable crimes.

1596
01:51:27,005 --> 01:51:28,093
I do.

1597
01:51:28,267 --> 01:51:29,355
Do you hate him?

1598
01:51:31,749 --> 01:51:32,750
I do.

1599
01:51:33,708 --> 01:51:37,059
And yet you are so calm
and unemotional

1600
01:51:37,146 --> 01:51:38,582
in your demeanor. Why?

1601
01:51:40,105 --> 01:51:42,717
Because your client
doesn't scare me anymore.

1602
01:51:44,370 --> 01:51:45,632
To what are you referring?

1603
01:51:47,069 --> 01:51:48,723
Ask your client. He'll remember.

1604
01:51:50,115 --> 01:51:52,248
KARL: Remember what, Mr. Bau?

1605
01:51:52,727 --> 01:51:56,469
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
The moment of my revenge.

1606
01:52:00,604 --> 01:52:02,519
Shall I elaborate?

1607
01:52:04,129 --> 01:52:06,131
Not at this time.

1608
01:52:08,177 --> 01:52:10,570
Reserve the right to re-cross,
Your Honor.

1609
01:52:10,657 --> 01:52:12,572
Your Honor,
I request a brief recess.

1610
01:52:12,703 --> 01:52:15,053
No, keep going. Talk to me.

1611
01:52:18,404 --> 01:52:21,407
Actually, uh, permission
to redirect, Your Honor.

1612
01:52:22,104 --> 01:52:23,148
Granted.

1613
01:52:25,847 --> 01:52:27,109
[MICHAEL CLEARS THROAT]

1614
01:52:33,158 --> 01:52:34,159
Mr. Bau...

1615
01:52:37,162 --> 01:52:40,252
have you ever actually seen
the defendant kill a person?

1616
01:52:41,514 --> 01:52:42,515
Yes.

1617
01:52:43,603 --> 01:52:45,518
He killed my father
right in front of me.

1618
01:52:45,649 --> 01:52:49,827
[AUDIENCE GASPING]

1619
01:52:50,132 --> 01:52:51,655
Would you be
all right describing

1620
01:52:51,742 --> 01:52:52,917
that experience for us?

1621
01:52:54,789 --> 01:52:55,964
I would.

1622
01:52:58,183 --> 01:53:01,578
The inciting incident
is actually quite amazing.

1623
01:53:01,970 --> 01:53:03,972
Amazing?
JOSEPH: Yes.

1624
01:53:04,973 --> 01:53:07,802
I'm an artist, so in the camp

1625
01:53:07,889 --> 01:53:09,891
I would occasionally
draw cartoons

1626
01:53:09,978 --> 01:53:11,762
for the other prisoners,
you know,

1627
01:53:12,284 --> 01:53:13,808
to keep up their spirits.

1628
01:53:14,547 --> 01:53:15,635
MICHAEL: Oh, cartoons?

1629
01:53:15,897 --> 01:53:19,161
Yes, mostly drawings
depicting the humiliation

1630
01:53:19,248 --> 01:53:22,033
of Nazi guards in various ways.

1631
01:53:22,338 --> 01:53:25,428
And since the defendant
was the most laughable

1632
01:53:25,515 --> 01:53:29,040
of the guards, by far,
he was frequently the object,

1633
01:53:29,606 --> 01:53:33,131
victim of our ridicule
and mockery.

1634
01:53:34,524 --> 01:53:36,004
MICHAEL: Mockery as to what?

1635
01:53:36,482 --> 01:53:40,356
Oh, his lack
of intelligence, mostly.

1636
01:53:41,183 --> 01:53:46,188
And his pitiful desperation
to impress superior officers.

1637
01:53:46,318 --> 01:53:49,408
Yeah,
principally Kommandant Goeth.

1638
01:53:49,669 --> 01:53:52,585
[AUDIENCE CHUCKLING]

1639
01:53:52,890 --> 01:53:56,372
Gruen was obsessed with seeking
the Kommandant's approval,

1640
01:53:56,459 --> 01:53:59,027
a task which he was never able
to accomplish.

1641
01:54:00,506 --> 01:54:04,293
That day, I had drawn
an especially accurate,

1642
01:54:04,467 --> 01:54:07,426
detailed rendering
of the defendant's face

1643
01:54:07,644 --> 01:54:09,515
on a roll of toilet paper.

1644
01:54:09,776 --> 01:54:11,213
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

1645
01:54:11,517 --> 01:54:12,562
JUDGE: Order!

1646
01:54:12,649 --> 01:54:13,868
Actually, it was of Hitler.

1647
01:54:15,043 --> 01:54:17,262
The defendant
will remain silent.

1648
01:54:17,393 --> 01:54:20,526
JOSEPH: I had shown the drawing
to dozens of prisoners already,

1649
01:54:20,744 --> 01:54:22,659
to an extraordinary reception.

1650
01:54:23,007 --> 01:54:25,488
You'd think I had painted
the Mona Lisa.

1651
01:54:26,010 --> 01:54:28,708
But do you know
who loved it most of all?

1652
01:54:30,623 --> 01:54:32,538
Kommandant Goeth.

1653
01:54:32,756 --> 01:54:35,498
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

1654
01:54:35,715 --> 01:54:38,631
I had shown it to the Kommandant
earlier that day.

1655
01:54:38,893 --> 01:54:40,764
Uh, I was his mapmaker, you see,

1656
01:54:40,895 --> 01:54:43,636
and so I had a lot of close,
personal contact with him.

1657
01:54:43,767 --> 01:54:45,290
We considered
each other friends.

1658
01:54:45,421 --> 01:54:49,381
[SCOFFS]
JOSEPH: He complained to me
often about Gruen.

1659
01:54:50,165 --> 01:54:53,472
When I showed him
this toilet paper masterpiece,

1660
01:54:53,864 --> 01:54:55,953
he found it
particularly amusing.

1661
01:54:56,040 --> 01:54:58,129
He actually asked me
to make copies for him,

1662
01:54:58,303 --> 01:55:00,566
one to keep,
and a number of extras,

1663
01:55:00,653 --> 01:55:03,743
which he said he wanted
to "give out to his friends."

1664
01:55:03,874 --> 01:55:07,791
I... I remember very clearly,
as I was leaving the room,

1665
01:55:08,096 --> 01:55:10,098
the Kommandant looked at
the drawing

1666
01:55:10,185 --> 01:55:12,143
and he said, laughing...

1667
01:55:13,188 --> 01:55:15,364
[IN GERMAN ACCENT]
"Right where he belongs."

1668
01:55:15,451 --> 01:55:17,801
"That piece of shit."

1669
01:55:17,932 --> 01:55:19,150
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]
JUDGE: Order.

1670
01:55:19,281 --> 01:55:20,412
Objection!
[GAVEL BANGING]

1671
01:55:20,499 --> 01:55:22,414
The witness
is provoking my client.

1672
01:55:22,588 --> 01:55:23,676
Overruled.

1673
01:55:24,025 --> 01:55:27,767
Would that be the, uh,
"Moment of revenge"

1674
01:55:27,985 --> 01:55:29,117
to which you referred?

1675
01:55:29,291 --> 01:55:33,338
Oh, no. Not even close.
It was a prelude.

1676
01:55:34,426 --> 01:55:38,691
Later on that day,
I was walking with my father,

1677
01:55:38,996 --> 01:55:41,956
and as I was showing him
the drawing it dropped.

1678
01:55:42,130 --> 01:55:44,045
The defendant
saw it on the ground.

1679
01:55:44,132 --> 01:55:47,396
The defendant was quite familiar
with my art

1680
01:55:47,613 --> 01:55:48,788
and knew it was my work.

1681
01:55:50,007 --> 01:55:54,185
But my sweet father
shouted that he had drawn it,

1682
01:55:54,751 --> 01:55:56,013
wanting to protect me.

1683
01:55:57,841 --> 01:56:00,975
But... didn't work.

1684
01:56:02,280 --> 01:56:03,281
No.

1685
01:56:04,282 --> 01:56:07,068
The defendant pulled
out his Luger...

1686
01:56:08,852 --> 01:56:11,028
and he said something
he must have felt was witty,

1687
01:56:11,115 --> 01:56:12,377
because he laughed.

1688
01:56:13,857 --> 01:56:14,989
But my father...

1689
01:56:17,469 --> 01:56:18,644
My poor father...

1690
01:56:21,952 --> 01:56:25,695
who had kept me
safe all my life.

1691
01:56:26,391 --> 01:56:28,959
Please. Papa, please.
Shh.

1692
01:56:29,264 --> 01:56:30,265
And?

1693
01:56:31,831 --> 01:56:33,355
Then he shot him in the face.

1694
01:56:33,964 --> 01:56:35,879
[AUDIENCE GASPING]

1695
01:56:36,053 --> 01:56:38,534
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1696
01:56:40,188 --> 01:56:41,189
[OSKAR EXHALES SHARPLY]

1697
01:56:43,104 --> 01:56:44,105
But then...

1698
01:56:45,236 --> 01:56:47,586
came the moment.

1699
01:56:51,286 --> 01:56:53,810
Do you want to tell this part,
Franz, or should I?

1700
01:56:53,897 --> 01:56:55,594
[GAVEL BANGS]

1701
01:56:55,681 --> 01:56:58,641
Witness shall direct comments
only to counsel.

1702
01:56:59,555 --> 01:57:00,904
What happened next, Mr. Bau?

1703
01:57:01,078 --> 01:57:06,344
Well, in a rage,
I threw myself at Gruen.

1704
01:57:06,562 --> 01:57:09,347
My body slammed into the gun,
he let go,

1705
01:57:09,434 --> 01:57:12,220
I grabbed it and smashed it
across his face!

1706
01:57:12,307 --> 01:57:14,613
You cannot possibly
believe this!
Order!

1707
01:57:14,744 --> 01:57:16,180
JOSEPH: I yanked his arm
with all my might

1708
01:57:16,267 --> 01:57:17,616
and he toppled off the horse.

1709
01:57:17,703 --> 01:57:19,923
Lies. This is a lie!
[GAVEL BANGS]

1710
01:57:20,010 --> 01:57:23,492
He was sprawled out in the snow,
and all the men were shouting,

1711
01:57:23,622 --> 01:57:26,190
"Kill him, kill him!"
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1712
01:57:26,277 --> 01:57:28,540
And I crushed the gun
against his ear,

1713
01:57:28,714 --> 01:57:30,064
right here! Right here!

1714
01:57:30,238 --> 01:57:33,284
You filthy lying Jew!
You stop this now!

1715
01:57:33,371 --> 01:57:35,417
Defendant will be held
in contempt of court

1716
01:57:35,504 --> 01:57:37,332
if there is one more outburst.

1717
01:57:37,462 --> 01:57:39,551
And a little blood
let out into the snow.

1718
01:57:40,030 --> 01:57:43,773
And I will never, never forget
the look in that man's eyes.

1719
01:57:43,947 --> 01:57:45,209
And what was that look?

1720
01:57:46,167 --> 01:57:49,779
Terror. Absolute terror.

1721
01:57:51,128 --> 01:57:54,218
I pistol whipped him again
against the side of the face,

1722
01:57:54,305 --> 01:57:56,046
and all the men
were around me screaming,

1723
01:57:56,177 --> 01:57:58,092
"Kill him! Kill him!"

1724
01:57:58,179 --> 01:58:00,137
And I put the muzzle
right in his eye,

1725
01:58:00,224 --> 01:58:03,445
and he was begging
for his life, crying,

1726
01:58:03,532 --> 01:58:04,968
tears running down his cheeks!

1727
01:58:05,055 --> 01:58:07,231
Whimpering and shaking
like a scared dog!

1728
01:58:07,405 --> 01:58:10,495
And I yelled at him, "I'm going
to shoot your face off!"

1729
01:58:10,582 --> 01:58:13,281
"This is how you die,
pleading for mercy,

1730
01:58:13,368 --> 01:58:16,632
helpless and alone,
beaten by the righteous hand

1731
01:58:16,719 --> 01:58:18,155
of a Jew!"

1732
01:58:18,373 --> 01:58:20,897
You lying kike!
Franz Gruen, sit down!

1733
01:58:21,027 --> 01:58:22,594
You begged for mercy!
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

1734
01:58:22,768 --> 01:58:27,121
I shot your weak, useless father
right in front of you!

1735
01:58:34,737 --> 01:58:37,827
There it is.
You weak Nazi coward.

1736
01:58:38,088 --> 01:58:39,742
I may be just one,

1737
01:58:39,829 --> 01:58:42,179
but I'm representing
six million more of these.

1738
01:58:42,266 --> 01:58:44,225
[AUDIENCE LAUGHS]

1739
01:58:44,486 --> 01:58:46,531
I should have killed you
when I had the chance.

1740
01:58:47,967 --> 01:58:49,969
I was a patriot!

1741
01:58:51,493 --> 01:58:54,191
Following orders.
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

1742
01:58:54,626 --> 01:58:57,760
I was... a patriot.

1743
01:58:58,761 --> 01:59:01,894
Guards, get this man out
of my courtroom immediately.

1744
01:59:02,765 --> 01:59:06,160
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

1745
01:59:07,813 --> 01:59:10,033
The witness is excused.

1746
01:59:11,904 --> 01:59:14,907
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

1747
01:59:33,796 --> 01:59:35,450
[MUSIC FADES]

1748
01:59:35,580 --> 01:59:38,801
[WHISTLES TUNE]

1749
01:59:41,499 --> 01:59:42,674
[BIRD CHIRPING]

1750
01:59:47,505 --> 01:59:51,422
